1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,360
The house near the Savannah River woke up slowly.

2
00:00:02,880 --> 00:00:06,220
The  way  old  houses  do,  carrying  the  habit  of  breathing  before

3
00:00:06,220 --> 00:00:06,800
their  people.

4
00:00:07,260 --> 00:00:10,640
The  light  of  dawn  came  through  the  crack  in  the  curtains  in  a  thin  strip

5
00:00:10,640 --> 00:00:11,660
and  settled  on

6
00:00:11,660 --> 00:00:14,800
her  shoulder,  and  Jago  Quint  stood  there  looking  at  that

7
00:00:14,800 --> 00:00:16,380
shoulder  for  longer  than  was  reasonable.

8
00:00:17,040 --> 00:00:20,080
Rowena  slept  on  her  side,  one  hand  opened  near  her

9
00:00:20,080 --> 00:00:21,780
face,  like  someone  who  had  left  a

10
00:00:21,780 --> 00:00:25,220
question half-assed and decided to finish asking at the next day.

11
00:00:25,220 --> 00:00:28,360
The  sheet  had  slipped  down  to  her  waist,  and  the  light

12
00:00:28,360 --> 00:00:29,920
caught  the  loose  strands  of  her  hair

13
00:00:29,920 --> 00:00:32,200
which still smelled of the soap from the night before.

14
00:00:32,640 --> 00:00:34,040
He got up without a sound.

15
00:00:34,540 --> 00:00:37,540
His  body  knew  this  ritual,  getting  out  of  bed  without

16
00:00:37,540 --> 00:00:38,740
waking  the  one  who  stayed.

17
00:00:39,220 --> 00:00:42,400
There  was  a  calm  inside  him  that  still  scared  him,  six  months

18
00:00:42,400 --> 00:00:43,940
after  she'd  moved  into  that  house.

19
00:00:44,320 --> 00:00:47,340
That  was  love  he'd  discovered,  and  at  the  same  time  it  was  something

20
00:00:47,340 --> 00:00:48,460
else  a  small  dread,

21
00:00:48,980 --> 00:00:52,120
almost  decorative  that  lived  beneath  his  rib  cage  and  beat  along

22
00:00:52,120 --> 00:00:52,880
with  his  heart.

23
00:00:53,280 --> 00:00:54,720
He thought he knew how to handle it.

24
00:00:54,720 --> 00:00:57,820
A  man  who  survived  what  he'd  survived,  learns  to

25
00:00:57,820 --> 00:00:58,900
tame  his  own  fear.

26
00:00:59,320 --> 00:01:02,400
He went down the stairs stepping on the side of the wood that didn't creak.

27
00:01:02,720 --> 00:01:07,840
The kitchen was still cold, with that stale air of June mornings that hadn't decided whether

28
00:01:07,840 --> 00:01:08,960
they were warm or not.

29
00:01:09,220 --> 00:01:13,780
He turned on the kettle, measured out her coffee like someone writing a sentence he already knew

30
00:01:13,780 --> 00:01:14,360
by heart.

31
00:01:14,820 --> 00:01:20,100
Two scoops of grounds, water that hadn't fully boiled, a little less than the usual ratio,

32
00:01:20,100 --> 00:01:24,900
because Roenah liked her coffee milder at the start of the day, as if the morning needed

33
00:01:24,900 --> 00:01:26,840
to ask permission before coming in.

34
00:01:27,340 --> 00:01:29,300
The smell rose slowly through the kitchen.

35
00:01:29,820 --> 00:01:31,920
There was something in it he could never quite name.

36
00:01:32,340 --> 00:01:33,660
It wasn't the coffee itself.

37
00:01:34,080 --> 00:01:35,740
It was what the smell stood for.

38
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:37,800
She was still there and she'd come down.

39
00:01:38,240 --> 00:01:41,840
There was a thought he avoided at that hour, and the thought showed up anyway.

40
00:01:42,260 --> 00:01:46,160
If she ever vanished from there the smell of coffee would tear him apart with devastating

41
00:01:46,160 --> 00:01:46,840
efficiency.

42
00:01:47,480 --> 00:01:51,860
He stirred the spoon slowly and brushed the thought aside with the same gesture you'd

43
00:01:51,860 --> 00:01:53,700
use to wave off a polite fly.

44
00:01:54,200 --> 00:01:54,760
Not today.

45
00:01:55,220 --> 00:01:56,240
The male came early.

46
00:01:56,760 --> 00:02:00,880
Feline, the personal assistant, delivered the envelope at the side door with the discrete

47
00:02:00,880 --> 00:02:03,180
punctuality J. Gopei dearly for.

48
00:02:03,440 --> 00:02:04,880
There were three letters from the office.

49
00:02:05,380 --> 00:02:08,880
One from the management of one of the properties, and a cream-coloured envelope.

50
00:02:09,240 --> 00:02:10,200
No return address.

51
00:02:10,760 --> 00:02:15,320
Address to Roenah Pike in the impersonal handwriting of a secretary at some respectable

52
00:02:15,320 --> 00:02:16,060
institution.

53
00:02:16,700 --> 00:02:20,140
He recognized the letterhead in the upper corner before he even looked properly.

54
00:02:20,660 --> 00:02:24,760
He stood there for a second with the envelope between his fingers, feeling the specific

55
00:02:24,760 --> 00:02:26,140
weight of quality paper.

56
00:02:26,640 --> 00:02:27,600
I'll take this one.

57
00:02:27,880 --> 00:02:28,820
He said, low.

58
00:02:29,300 --> 00:02:33,460
He tucked the envelope into the inside pocket of his jacket, as if he were putting away

59
00:02:33,460 --> 00:02:36,100
an important document he'd remember to hand over later.

60
00:02:36,520 --> 00:02:37,780
In New He wouldn't remember.

61
00:02:38,360 --> 00:02:41,800
He'd already decided not to remember before he even finished the gesture.

62
00:02:41,800 --> 00:02:46,360
The worst part was that his hand had made the move without consulting him, with an old

63
00:02:46,360 --> 00:02:49,980
efficiency he recognized as his own, and didn't like recognizing.

64
00:02:50,760 --> 00:02:51,620
Feline saw it.

65
00:02:52,020 --> 00:02:52,880
Feline said nothing.

66
00:02:53,440 --> 00:02:57,940
The two exchanged a brief greeting, and the assistant left the same way he'd come in,

67
00:02:58,280 --> 00:03:00,280
is steps muffled by the runner in the hallway.

68
00:03:00,760 --> 00:03:03,940
When Roenah came down, coffee was served in two cups.

69
00:03:04,420 --> 00:03:07,540
She appeared in the kitchen doorway, in a long night gown.

70
00:03:07,540 --> 00:03:12,360
A hair loosely pinned up, rubbing her eye with a closed fist like a child.

71
00:03:12,840 --> 00:03:17,340
The morning sun was coming in now through the side window, and drew a golden square on

72
00:03:17,340 --> 00:03:18,840
the wooden floor between them.

73
00:03:19,040 --> 00:03:23,120
He looked up and the small decorative dread settled back beneath his ribcage quiet.

74
00:03:23,660 --> 00:03:24,260
You got up early?

75
00:03:24,720 --> 00:03:27,100
She remarked, her voice still thick with sleep.

76
00:03:27,520 --> 00:03:32,120
I couldn't sleep with you breathing so beautifully like that, J. Go answered, and his mouth

77
00:03:32,120 --> 00:03:33,020
almost smiled.

78
00:03:33,540 --> 00:03:34,080
She laughed.

79
00:03:34,080 --> 00:03:38,560
It was a short, slightly husky laugh, the kind he collected inside without admitting

80
00:03:38,560 --> 00:03:39,700
he collected them.

81
00:03:39,900 --> 00:03:44,460
She sat on the stool at the kitchen island, took the cup with both hands, and smelled

82
00:03:44,460 --> 00:03:46,920
it before drinking the way she did every day.

83
00:03:47,280 --> 00:03:52,300
Her eyes closing for half a second over the steam, a gesture so hers that he already knew

84
00:03:52,300 --> 00:03:53,020
it by heart.

85
00:03:53,400 --> 00:03:54,980
He watched without seeming to watch.

86
00:03:55,440 --> 00:03:56,960
Are you expecting anything today?

87
00:03:57,180 --> 00:04:00,460
He asked, and the tone was casual in that practiced way.

88
00:04:00,460 --> 00:04:05,760
Rowena thought for a second her eyes still on the cup, and answer, she said, maybe.

89
00:04:06,140 --> 00:04:09,480
That conversation I told you about last week, she looked up.

90
00:04:09,680 --> 00:04:10,280
You remember?

91
00:04:10,840 --> 00:04:12,300
I remember, he answered.

92
00:04:12,820 --> 00:04:13,260
He remembered.

93
00:04:13,860 --> 00:04:18,420
In his pocket he had exactly the answer she was waiting for, and the answer was generous.

94
00:04:18,940 --> 00:04:21,580
And the answer would take her out of that house for six months.

95
00:04:22,140 --> 00:04:24,320
The pocket weighed on him in a specific way.

96
00:04:24,680 --> 00:04:26,940
He drank his own coffee and said nothing more.

97
00:04:27,520 --> 00:04:29,820
Rowena looked at him for a second longer than her usual.

98
00:04:29,820 --> 00:04:34,260
Then she looked at her own coffee, and the rest of the morning ran along beautifully,

99
00:04:34,880 --> 00:04:36,720
the way their mornings usually ran.

100
00:04:37,160 --> 00:04:41,260
At noon, Silas Ashford was waiting for Jago at the office in downtown Savannah.

101
00:04:41,780 --> 00:04:45,460
The lawyer had a way of sitting in chairs that didn't belong to him as if they did.

102
00:04:45,760 --> 00:04:48,640
Legs crossed, one finger resting against his temple.

103
00:04:49,120 --> 00:04:51,940
The expressionless face he wore when he brought bad news.

104
00:04:52,380 --> 00:04:56,580
The air conditioning in the room was set too high, and the artificial chill clashed

105
00:04:56,580 --> 00:04:59,780
with the heat coming in through the wide windows overlooking the square.

106
00:05:00,360 --> 00:05:00,840
Short lunch.

107
00:05:01,380 --> 00:05:03,220
Silas announced when Jago walked in.

108
00:05:03,660 --> 00:05:04,180
Short why?

109
00:05:04,680 --> 00:05:07,320
Because what I've got to tell you doesn't go well with dessert.

110
00:05:07,920 --> 00:05:09,620
Jago closed the door behind him.

111
00:05:09,760 --> 00:05:11,620
He sat down on the other side of the desk.

112
00:05:12,080 --> 00:05:14,580
The two had no need to other long enough to skip the run around.

113
00:05:15,200 --> 00:05:16,400
Someone's asking questions.

114
00:05:16,980 --> 00:05:18,480
Silas said without raising his voice.

115
00:05:18,880 --> 00:05:20,320
Again in three different places.

116
00:05:20,960 --> 00:05:21,820
Discrete questions.

117
00:05:22,260 --> 00:05:23,600
The kind of trained person asks.

118
00:05:23,600 --> 00:05:27,980
And the questions come too close to what we agreed to never let anyone get close to.

119
00:05:28,220 --> 00:05:29,240
Jago didn't move.

120
00:05:29,700 --> 00:05:31,720
Inside the decorative dread grew an inch.

121
00:05:32,260 --> 00:05:32,540
Name?

122
00:05:33,080 --> 00:05:33,380
He asked.

123
00:05:33,840 --> 00:05:34,320
Not yet.

124
00:05:34,720 --> 00:05:37,780
But they pay well, and they pay with money that leaves no trail.

125
00:05:38,180 --> 00:05:39,780
That interest me more than the name.

126
00:05:40,240 --> 00:05:41,420
Jago looked at the desk.

127
00:05:41,820 --> 00:05:44,120
There was a line of silence the two of them respected.

128
00:05:44,700 --> 00:05:46,560
The kind built over years of loyalty.

129
00:05:47,200 --> 00:05:47,820
Silas waited.

130
00:05:48,320 --> 00:05:52,320
He always waited with that stone patience he charged dearly for by the hour.

131
00:05:52,320 --> 00:05:54,440
Double the security at the house.

132
00:05:54,720 --> 00:05:55,720
Jago said finally.

133
00:05:56,580 --> 00:05:57,140
Quietly.

134
00:05:57,420 --> 00:05:58,480
Rowina can't know.

135
00:05:58,920 --> 00:06:01,160
Silas kept looking at him a second longer than necessary.

136
00:06:01,800 --> 00:06:02,220
Jago.

137
00:06:02,720 --> 00:06:03,920
She can't know Silas.

138
00:06:04,420 --> 00:06:07,340
The lawyer ran his tongue along the inside corner of his cheek.

139
00:06:07,740 --> 00:06:11,500
A small gesture he made when he wanted to say something and chose not to.

140
00:06:11,780 --> 00:06:14,580
Then he nodded in that short dry way of his.

141
00:06:14,980 --> 00:06:16,920
And that envelope, Silas asked.

142
00:06:17,360 --> 00:06:18,420
Did the answer come?

143
00:06:18,880 --> 00:06:20,400
Jago didn't answer right away.

144
00:06:20,400 --> 00:06:23,740
He tapped his thumb lightly on the tabletop once twice.

145
00:06:24,380 --> 00:06:24,920
It came.

146
00:06:25,340 --> 00:06:26,620
Are you going to deliver it?

147
00:06:26,840 --> 00:06:27,440
I am.

148
00:06:28,620 --> 00:06:29,420
Jago looked up.

149
00:06:29,720 --> 00:06:33,020
There was something in his eyes that Silas had known long before this conversation.

150
00:06:33,620 --> 00:06:36,340
The same thing that lived in that gaze ten years ago.

151
00:06:36,600 --> 00:06:39,520
And that Silas had hoped for a while had gotten better.

152
00:06:39,920 --> 00:06:41,300
When I figure out how.

153
00:06:41,800 --> 00:06:42,460
Silas nodded.

154
00:06:42,800 --> 00:06:43,900
But his face didn't agree.

155
00:06:44,440 --> 00:06:48,500
The two finished lunch in decent silence with the noise from the square coming in muffled

156
00:06:48,500 --> 00:06:49,200
through the windows.

157
00:06:49,200 --> 00:06:54,000
When Jago left the office, the cream envelope was still weighing in the inside pocket

158
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:54,620
of his jacket.

159
00:06:55,100 --> 00:06:59,780
And he had for the first time in a long time a brief urge to tear it up.

160
00:07:00,160 --> 00:07:03,060
Rowena spent the afternoon in the living room of the house near the river.

161
00:07:03,520 --> 00:07:05,340
She was rereading some old work notes.

162
00:07:05,700 --> 00:07:09,360
Things she kept in a hardcover folder that sat on a shelf in plain sight.

163
00:07:09,680 --> 00:07:10,920
No hiding place at all.

164
00:07:11,300 --> 00:07:15,780
She'd learned to value that transparency the way people do, who have already lost someone

165
00:07:15,780 --> 00:07:17,100
by hiding too much.

166
00:07:17,100 --> 00:07:22,040
The afternoon light came in slanted through the half open blinds and striped the rug in

167
00:07:22,040 --> 00:07:22,900
golden bands.

168
00:07:23,440 --> 00:07:28,140
Outside the river made its usual gentle sound, the living room phone rang at a little

169
00:07:28,140 --> 00:07:29,000
past five.

170
00:07:29,420 --> 00:07:31,120
Nieve had gone to the market with Feline.

171
00:07:31,720 --> 00:07:33,260
Jago hadn't come back yet.

172
00:07:33,700 --> 00:07:34,360
Rowena answered.

173
00:07:34,880 --> 00:07:35,560
Quint residence.

174
00:07:36,120 --> 00:07:36,560
She said.

175
00:07:36,880 --> 00:07:38,040
The way she always answered.

176
00:07:38,380 --> 00:07:39,880
Half joking with the formality.

177
00:07:40,440 --> 00:07:43,040
On the other end, a full second of silence.

178
00:07:43,040 --> 00:07:46,500
Then a man's voice horse with age and with something harder to name.

179
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:48,860
Good afternoon I need to speak with Mr. Quint.

180
00:07:49,420 --> 00:07:50,300
He's not in at the moment.

181
00:07:50,560 --> 00:07:51,460
Can I take a message?

182
00:07:52,080 --> 00:07:52,760
Another silence.

183
00:07:53,420 --> 00:07:56,820
She heard the man breathe as if he were weighing every word before letting it out.

184
00:07:57,420 --> 00:08:01,660
Rowena, a well-trained journalist, began paying attention with her whole body.

185
00:08:02,100 --> 00:08:03,420
Without yet knowing why.

186
00:08:03,860 --> 00:08:06,460
There was something in that silence that wasn't in decision.

187
00:08:07,040 --> 00:08:08,040
It was calculation.

188
00:08:08,980 --> 00:08:10,620
It's the man coughed lightly.

189
00:08:11,120 --> 00:08:12,000
It's about kit.

190
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:14,100
Tell him it's about kit.

191
00:08:14,360 --> 00:08:15,060
He'll understand.

192
00:08:15,820 --> 00:08:17,400
Rowena stopped breathing for a second.

193
00:08:17,920 --> 00:08:19,060
Not because of the name.

194
00:08:19,500 --> 00:08:21,200
The name still meant nothing to her.

195
00:08:21,380 --> 00:08:23,500
She stopped because of the way the man said it.

196
00:08:23,840 --> 00:08:28,320
Like someone handing over a password, he knows will open a door that's been locked for a long time.

197
00:08:28,860 --> 00:08:33,240
Kit, she repeated slowly and her voice came out more neutral than she was feeling.

198
00:08:33,880 --> 00:08:35,060
May I ask who's calling?

199
00:08:35,580 --> 00:08:38,060
The man was already answering when the front door slammed.

200
00:08:38,600 --> 00:08:39,660
Quick steps in the hallway.

201
00:08:39,660 --> 00:08:42,820
Quicker than J. GO step usually was at the end of the day.

202
00:08:43,140 --> 00:08:46,180
He walked into the room with his meeting posture still in his body.

203
00:08:46,560 --> 00:08:48,920
And stopped walking when he saw the phone in her hand.

204
00:08:49,340 --> 00:08:52,700
She watched the colour drain from his face in real time.

205
00:08:53,000 --> 00:08:55,760
It was something she'd never seen before in that man.

206
00:08:56,240 --> 00:08:58,480
No anger, no practice, surprise.

207
00:08:59,000 --> 00:09:01,020
Just a physical animal whiteness.

208
00:09:01,280 --> 00:09:05,620
Rising from his chin to his forehead in seconds, as if someone had flipped a switch.

209
00:09:06,140 --> 00:09:06,880
The was it?

210
00:09:07,100 --> 00:09:07,540
He asked.

211
00:09:07,540 --> 00:09:10,180
His voice too low for the size of the question.

212
00:09:10,820 --> 00:09:11,800
Roena didn't answer.

213
00:09:12,180 --> 00:09:13,100
She held out the receiver.

214
00:09:13,740 --> 00:09:16,620
J. GO took it, brought it to his ear, listened for two seconds.

215
00:09:17,260 --> 00:09:20,500
Close his eyes once. A single blink longer than normal.

216
00:09:20,940 --> 00:09:23,400
The kind of gesture that isn't reflex its decision.

217
00:09:24,000 --> 00:09:25,480
And then said just one sentence.

218
00:09:26,040 --> 00:09:27,080
Don't call this number.

219
00:09:27,540 --> 00:09:28,220
He hung up.

220
00:09:28,420 --> 00:09:32,460
He kept his hand on the phone for a length of time she counted inside her own chest.

221
00:09:32,740 --> 00:09:33,580
Be it by beat.

222
00:09:34,180 --> 00:09:35,360
Roena looked at him.

223
00:09:35,480 --> 00:09:37,060
She knew that man in her body.

224
00:09:37,060 --> 00:09:38,140
In his smell.

225
00:09:38,560 --> 00:09:41,220
In the way he ran his thumb under his eye when he was tired.

226
00:09:41,700 --> 00:09:43,420
She'd never seen him white like that.

227
00:09:43,640 --> 00:09:46,220
She'd never seen him need support just to stay standing.

228
00:09:46,800 --> 00:09:47,480
J. GO.

229
00:09:47,800 --> 00:09:48,960
He didn't answer right away.

230
00:09:49,340 --> 00:09:49,960
Who was it?

231
00:09:50,180 --> 00:09:50,660
She asked.

232
00:09:51,080 --> 00:09:53,940
With the trained calm her profession had given her as a gift.

233
00:09:54,400 --> 00:09:55,200
He looked up.

234
00:09:55,420 --> 00:09:56,840
And that was when she saw it.

235
00:09:57,200 --> 00:09:59,160
For the first time since the two of them had met,

236
00:09:59,520 --> 00:10:01,100
she saw him decide to lie.

237
00:10:01,540 --> 00:10:02,700
It wasn't a quick decision.

238
00:10:03,260 --> 00:10:04,780
She saw the moment before it.

239
00:10:04,780 --> 00:10:07,600
The instant when he could still choose the other path.

240
00:10:07,900 --> 00:10:09,720
An old employee, J. GO said,

241
00:10:10,100 --> 00:10:12,080
drunk probably got the wrong number.

242
00:10:12,440 --> 00:10:13,680
She kept looking at him.

243
00:10:13,960 --> 00:10:17,480
He held her gaze with the composure of someone who'd spent his whole life holding

244
00:10:17,480 --> 00:10:18,180
gayses.

245
00:10:18,480 --> 00:10:19,580
He couldn't afford to lose.

246
00:10:20,140 --> 00:10:22,160
He knew inside that she knew.

247
00:10:22,600 --> 00:10:24,820
Still, he wanted her to let it go.

248
00:10:25,200 --> 00:10:26,940
He said a name, Roena said,

249
00:10:27,400 --> 00:10:29,740
and her voice came out very low almost gentle,

250
00:10:30,180 --> 00:10:32,540
which was the way she used when the question wasn't gentle.

251
00:10:33,020 --> 00:10:33,740
J. GO swallowed.

252
00:10:33,740 --> 00:10:34,780
What name?

253
00:10:35,320 --> 00:10:35,500
Kid.

254
00:10:36,060 --> 00:10:36,740
He didn't blink.

255
00:10:37,180 --> 00:10:39,740
He carried his body to the sideboard next to the sofa,

256
00:10:40,340 --> 00:10:42,840
rested his hand on the wood as if he needed something solid.

257
00:10:43,300 --> 00:10:46,800
And spoke looking at the river through the window, his back to her.

258
00:10:47,000 --> 00:10:48,200
I don't know him.

259
00:10:48,520 --> 00:10:49,840
Roena stood where she was.

260
00:10:50,260 --> 00:10:53,140
On the other side of the room near the big window there was a chair.

261
00:10:53,660 --> 00:10:55,680
Just like the one in the mansion's main hall,

262
00:10:56,160 --> 00:10:57,740
brought here when they moved in.

263
00:10:57,940 --> 00:11:02,780
She had now six months of looking at that chair without understanding why no one ever sat in it.

264
00:11:02,780 --> 00:11:05,520
Why the seat was always turned slightly toward the river,

265
00:11:05,940 --> 00:11:08,700
as if waiting for someone who knew where they'd arrived from.

266
00:11:08,880 --> 00:11:11,700
She looked at the chair, looked at J. GO's back,

267
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:13,100
looked at the chair again,

268
00:11:13,440 --> 00:11:15,720
and the chair for the first time had a sound.

269
00:11:16,260 --> 00:11:19,080
The name was short, short, and old.

270
00:11:19,480 --> 00:11:23,940
It had only three letters, and it slipped down the phone line like a poorly tied secret,

271
00:11:24,400 --> 00:11:25,720
spoken by a horse voice.

272
00:11:26,260 --> 00:11:26,520
Kid.

273
00:11:27,020 --> 00:11:28,400
She didn't repeat it out loud.

274
00:11:28,840 --> 00:11:29,660
She kept it.

275
00:11:29,820 --> 00:11:31,160
She was very good at that.

276
00:11:31,160 --> 00:11:33,100
That night Roena didn't sleep.

277
00:11:33,460 --> 00:11:35,260
She lay looking at the bedroom ceiling,

278
00:11:35,780 --> 00:11:37,620
listening to his breathing beside her.

279
00:11:37,840 --> 00:11:39,940
That breathing she knew better than her own,

280
00:11:40,300 --> 00:11:42,180
that she could tell when it was real sleep,

281
00:11:42,440 --> 00:11:43,440
and when it was faked.

282
00:11:43,940 --> 00:11:46,340
That night for the first time she couldn't read it.

283
00:11:46,560 --> 00:11:50,040
Outside, the river ran with its usual soft sound,

284
00:11:50,580 --> 00:11:53,560
indifferent to what was happening inside that beautiful house.

285
00:11:54,040 --> 00:11:57,060
Inside her chest, an empty chair had begun to creak.

286
00:11:57,440 --> 00:12:00,220
The sun came into the bedroom in the morning as if nothing had happened,

287
00:12:00,220 --> 00:12:03,120
and Jago moved in bed the way he always did.

288
00:12:03,460 --> 00:12:05,740
His hand seeking her waist beneath the sheet,

289
00:12:06,240 --> 00:12:08,420
his face pressing into the nape of her neck,

290
00:12:08,840 --> 00:12:11,520
the short kiss at the spot where her hair began.

291
00:12:12,220 --> 00:12:16,220
Roena lay still, eyes closed, and received it all with her skin.

292
00:12:16,680 --> 00:12:17,900
His warmth was real.

293
00:12:18,320 --> 00:12:19,960
The weight of his arm was real.

294
00:12:20,380 --> 00:12:22,720
It was easier to stay quiet a second longer,

295
00:12:23,160 --> 00:12:26,440
and let her body believe in what her mind hadn't yet resolved.

296
00:12:27,000 --> 00:12:28,060
Then she turned over.

297
00:12:28,400 --> 00:12:28,860
Jago.

298
00:12:29,540 --> 00:12:30,820
The call yesterday.

299
00:12:31,280 --> 00:12:33,620
He opened his eyes with a staged laziness.

300
00:12:34,140 --> 00:12:35,000
She saw the staging.

301
00:12:35,480 --> 00:12:38,640
It was quick, almost imperceptible, but she saw it.

302
00:12:38,840 --> 00:12:42,520
She'd learn to see the small things in him before she'd learn their names.

303
00:12:43,020 --> 00:12:44,960
I already told you my love, it was nobody.

304
00:12:45,500 --> 00:12:46,280
You went white.

305
00:12:46,720 --> 00:12:48,500
Jago smiled with half his mouth.

306
00:12:48,800 --> 00:12:51,040
That small smile he reserved for diffusing

307
00:12:51,040 --> 00:12:53,140
difficult situations in boardrooms.

308
00:12:53,460 --> 00:12:56,480
He raised his hand and tucked a strand of her hair behind her ear,

309
00:12:56,900 --> 00:12:58,360
with a calculated lightness.

310
00:12:58,360 --> 00:13:00,940
A gesture that had always worked before.

311
00:13:01,300 --> 00:13:03,720
One she herself had loved in those first months,

312
00:13:04,140 --> 00:13:06,120
when she still couldn't tell genuine tenderness

313
00:13:06,120 --> 00:13:08,380
from the tenderness that served as a curtain.

314
00:13:08,840 --> 00:13:11,820
I didn't, he said, his voice low and firm,

315
00:13:12,340 --> 00:13:13,440
you were against the light.

316
00:13:13,920 --> 00:13:15,100
She looked at him in silence.

317
00:13:15,760 --> 00:13:17,600
A pause of three, four seconds,

318
00:13:18,100 --> 00:13:21,200
enough for any guilty person to fill the emptiness with more words.

319
00:13:21,500 --> 00:13:23,360
He didn't fill it, he was too good for that.

320
00:13:23,560 --> 00:13:26,680
He leaned in, kissed the corner of her mouth with a tenderness

321
00:13:26,680 --> 00:13:29,500
that was real and at the same time evasive about everything,

322
00:13:30,040 --> 00:13:31,420
and spoke against her skin.

323
00:13:31,820 --> 00:13:32,660
Let's have coffee.

324
00:13:33,300 --> 00:13:34,220
Rowena let it go.

325
00:13:34,620 --> 00:13:35,500
She kissed him back.

326
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:38,460
Short, got up, went to shower alone.

327
00:13:38,980 --> 00:13:41,120
And while the water fell too hot on her shoulders,

328
00:13:41,640 --> 00:13:44,080
she thought for the first time in plain terms,

329
00:13:44,420 --> 00:13:46,240
a sentence that bothered her a great deal.

330
00:13:46,800 --> 00:13:49,760
Tenderness and truth are not the same thing.

331
00:13:49,980 --> 00:13:52,580
She stayed under the water longer than she needed to.

332
00:13:52,860 --> 00:13:56,460
The bathroom smelled of the citrus soap Jago had started buying for her,

333
00:13:56,460 --> 00:13:58,300
when he noticed which one she liked.

334
00:13:58,860 --> 00:14:00,320
One more detail he memorized,

335
00:14:00,920 --> 00:14:03,540
one more gesture she no longer knew how to receive.

336
00:14:03,940 --> 00:14:05,740
She came down dressed to go out.

337
00:14:06,100 --> 00:14:08,200
Linin pants, a light-colored blouse.

338
00:14:08,640 --> 00:14:10,620
A small bag she used when she went downtown.

339
00:14:11,240 --> 00:14:13,440
Jago was in the kitchen reading something on the tablet,

340
00:14:13,740 --> 00:14:17,460
with a cup of coffee in front of him that must have been half-loop warm by now.

341
00:14:17,740 --> 00:14:21,200
He looked at her with that gaze that crossed the room without needing distance.

342
00:14:21,660 --> 00:14:22,500
Where are you going?

343
00:14:22,900 --> 00:14:25,140
She founded him using, not the question.

344
00:14:25,140 --> 00:14:26,220
The tone.

345
00:14:26,780 --> 00:14:27,940
It was his old tone.

346
00:14:28,340 --> 00:14:31,780
The one she thought had been left behind since they'd gotten themselves organized,

347
00:14:32,480 --> 00:14:34,820
six months earlier, to live together there near the river.

348
00:14:35,340 --> 00:14:37,220
Downtown, by a couple things.

349
00:14:37,800 --> 00:14:39,180
Marlo arrives today, remember?

350
00:14:39,720 --> 00:14:40,320
I remember.

351
00:14:40,900 --> 00:14:41,760
He set down the tablet.

352
00:14:42,340 --> 00:14:43,140
Taking the car?

353
00:14:43,580 --> 00:14:44,600
I'm driving myself.

354
00:14:45,120 --> 00:14:47,000
He nodded as if he were accepting it.

355
00:14:47,240 --> 00:14:48,080
He reached out.

356
00:14:48,300 --> 00:14:50,220
Took a hand on the cold marble counter,

357
00:14:50,880 --> 00:14:51,620
squeezed it lightly.

358
00:14:52,100 --> 00:14:54,940
His fingers wrapping around hers with the ease of someone

359
00:14:54,940 --> 00:14:56,780
who already knew every knuckle.

360
00:14:57,260 --> 00:14:57,680
Be careful.

361
00:14:59,180 --> 00:15:00,380
She went out the side door.

362
00:15:00,820 --> 00:15:02,920
She walked along the stone hallway to the garage,

363
00:15:03,360 --> 00:15:04,680
took the keys off the hook.

364
00:15:05,120 --> 00:15:07,520
The air outside smelled of the river's dampness,

365
00:15:07,800 --> 00:15:10,420
and of some neighbouring garden that must have had Jasmine.

366
00:15:10,960 --> 00:15:14,060
It was early enough that Savannah's heat hadn't yet weighed down.

367
00:15:14,400 --> 00:15:15,920
When she opened the electric gate,

368
00:15:16,340 --> 00:15:20,180
two men in suits were standing outside next to a dark car she didn't recognize.

369
00:15:20,780 --> 00:15:22,140
They didn't seem like a threat.

370
00:15:22,500 --> 00:15:23,480
They seemed like scenery.

371
00:15:23,480 --> 00:15:25,820
The scenery of another kind of house,

372
00:15:26,080 --> 00:15:26,720
not hers.

373
00:15:27,280 --> 00:15:29,600
One of them approached with a smile that was too polite.

374
00:15:30,180 --> 00:15:32,360
Mrs. Pike, good morning, will be going with you.

375
00:15:32,660 --> 00:15:33,560
Rowena blinked.

376
00:15:33,820 --> 00:15:34,900
Going with me, where?

377
00:15:35,300 --> 00:15:36,120
Wherever you go.

378
00:15:36,420 --> 00:15:36,940
House orders.

379
00:15:37,480 --> 00:15:37,800
Security.

380
00:15:38,420 --> 00:15:39,400
She looked at the man.

381
00:15:39,760 --> 00:15:40,820
Looked at the other one.

382
00:15:41,180 --> 00:15:42,540
Neither of them seemed embarrassed.

383
00:15:43,140 --> 00:15:45,200
Neither of them seemed to expect her to argue.

384
00:15:45,720 --> 00:15:48,180
That more than anything else was what bothered her,

385
00:15:48,400 --> 00:15:52,160
that they derived ready for the normalcy of a situation she hadn't authorized.

386
00:15:52,160 --> 00:15:54,080
I didn't ask for security.

387
00:15:54,620 --> 00:15:57,280
She said, with a calm that wasn't easy to maintain.

388
00:15:57,780 --> 00:16:00,260
You don't need to ask, Mom, it's already been arranged.

389
00:16:00,760 --> 00:16:02,720
She stood for a second on the stone pavement.

390
00:16:03,280 --> 00:16:06,300
Inside the house, behind her, Jago knew.

391
00:16:06,780 --> 00:16:09,540
Jago was on the tablet with the lukewarm cup, and he knew.

392
00:16:09,900 --> 00:16:12,660
It given the order the day before at the downtown office,

393
00:16:13,020 --> 00:16:16,220
and he knew the exact second she'd meet those two men at the gate.

394
00:16:16,640 --> 00:16:19,140
At that very moment, sitting in the kitchen,

395
00:16:19,140 --> 00:16:22,860
he swallowed some coffee that was too cold to cover his own nerves.

396
00:16:23,400 --> 00:16:26,560
His hand pressing lightly on the tablet for no reason at all.

397
00:16:26,980 --> 00:16:28,140
Rowena didn't make a scene.

398
00:16:28,500 --> 00:16:31,760
She simply said, All right, she got into her car.

399
00:16:32,080 --> 00:16:33,460
Let their car follow behind.

400
00:16:34,000 --> 00:16:36,740
She drove to downtown Savannah with both hands on the wheel,

401
00:16:37,180 --> 00:16:39,380
and the silence inside the car so vast,

402
00:16:39,880 --> 00:16:41,000
that she turned on the radio.

403
00:16:41,560 --> 00:16:42,760
Found it unbearable.

404
00:16:43,240 --> 00:16:44,020
Turned it off.

405
00:16:44,380 --> 00:16:46,260
Bahan stayed on the leather of the wheel,

406
00:16:46,260 --> 00:16:50,180
and she looked out the window at the old Magnolia's lining the avenue.

407
00:16:50,860 --> 00:16:52,540
White and heavy from so much blooming,

408
00:16:53,100 --> 00:16:55,940
and thought that some beautiful things were also suffocating.

409
00:16:56,460 --> 00:16:59,880
Marlo Trent showed up on time at the old cafe in the historic district,

410
00:17:00,380 --> 00:17:03,320
with a bag too big for anything she could possibly need there,

411
00:17:03,600 --> 00:17:06,340
and an expression Rowena recognized from far off.

412
00:17:06,720 --> 00:17:09,040
The expression of someone who'd flown three hours

413
00:17:09,040 --> 00:17:12,340
to give a dose of reality to someone she loved very much,

414
00:17:12,560 --> 00:17:14,100
and who was in need of hearing it.

415
00:17:14,400 --> 00:17:15,560
Row, Marlo,

416
00:17:15,560 --> 00:17:17,960
they hugged the way they'd hugged for years,

417
00:17:18,340 --> 00:17:19,300
tight without ceremony.

418
00:17:19,960 --> 00:17:23,100
Marlo rubbing her hand twice on her back with that energy of someone who

419
00:17:23,100 --> 00:17:24,280
arrived to fix something.

420
00:17:24,740 --> 00:17:28,500
The cafe smelled of cinnamon and burnt coffee from an old machine,

421
00:17:29,000 --> 00:17:31,840
and the dark wooden tables had marks from years of cups.

422
00:17:32,240 --> 00:17:33,240
They sat near the window.

423
00:17:33,880 --> 00:17:35,060
Marlo ordered black coffee,

424
00:17:35,660 --> 00:17:36,780
Rowena a cappuccino.

425
00:17:37,380 --> 00:17:40,200
Across the street, the dark car parked with professional discretion.

426
00:17:40,840 --> 00:17:43,480
Those two yours, Marlo pointed with her chin,

427
00:17:43,860 --> 00:17:44,800
no filter at all.

428
00:17:44,800 --> 00:17:46,020
They're the houses,

429
00:17:46,600 --> 00:17:47,180
the houses.

430
00:17:47,880 --> 00:17:49,760
Yeah, Marlo raised a eyebrow.

431
00:17:50,520 --> 00:17:52,960
Marlo had an eyebrow that asked whole questions on its own

432
00:17:52,960 --> 00:17:54,540
without needing anything more.

433
00:17:54,880 --> 00:17:56,280
Row, don't start.

434
00:17:56,880 --> 00:17:58,920
Row, love doesn't treat you like a hostage.

435
00:17:59,620 --> 00:18:00,260
Rowena loved.

436
00:18:00,780 --> 00:18:03,060
It was a short laugh a little awkward but honest,

437
00:18:03,560 --> 00:18:05,340
and she felt along with it a good pang.

438
00:18:05,820 --> 00:18:08,080
The pang of someone being reminded of herself

439
00:18:08,080 --> 00:18:10,620
by someone who'd known her before all of this.

440
00:18:10,880 --> 00:18:12,220
They talked for an hour.

441
00:18:12,220 --> 00:18:14,200
Marlo talked about the newsroom,

442
00:18:14,560 --> 00:18:17,040
about the new editor who'd reorganized everything.

443
00:18:17,460 --> 00:18:22,400
About the people who still asked about Rowena now and then with that mix of curiosity and respect

444
00:18:22,400 --> 00:18:24,600
that comes just before being forgotten.

445
00:18:25,140 --> 00:18:27,940
Rowena listened and wanted to feel a clean kind of longing,

446
00:18:28,600 --> 00:18:32,060
uncomplicated, but the longing that arrived had an uneven edge.

447
00:18:32,460 --> 00:18:34,340
At some point, out of old reflex,

448
00:18:34,960 --> 00:18:36,540
she took the recorder from her bag.

449
00:18:36,900 --> 00:18:41,280
A small, silver recorder that she carried out of a habit of more than six years,

450
00:18:41,280 --> 00:18:42,940
always in the side pocket.

451
00:18:43,380 --> 00:18:45,560
She looked at the device in the palm of her hand

452
00:18:45,560 --> 00:18:48,300
as if she weren't sure when it had ended up there.

453
00:18:48,560 --> 00:18:50,960
She put it back without pressing a single button.

454
00:18:51,460 --> 00:18:52,320
Marlo saw it.

455
00:18:52,680 --> 00:18:54,740
Marlo saw everything always had.

456
00:18:55,060 --> 00:18:56,320
Who are you now journalist?

457
00:18:56,620 --> 00:19:01,240
She asked, with the corner of her mouth croaked in a way that was both a question and a fiction,

458
00:19:01,840 --> 00:19:06,080
Rowena laughed for real this time, a bigger laugh that arrived without warning.

459
00:19:06,580 --> 00:19:09,420
A woman waiting for an answer that never comes.

460
00:19:09,420 --> 00:19:10,460
What answer?

461
00:19:10,960 --> 00:19:11,540
A proposal?

462
00:19:12,140 --> 00:19:12,800
A job offer?

463
00:19:13,200 --> 00:19:14,320
They sent it last week.

464
00:19:14,780 --> 00:19:16,220
I still haven't gotten any reply.

465
00:19:16,840 --> 00:19:18,240
Marlo kept looking at her.

466
00:19:18,460 --> 00:19:21,920
She held the cup with both hands and waited a second longer before speaking.

467
00:19:22,440 --> 00:19:23,780
That second rowing a new.

468
00:19:24,260 --> 00:19:27,080
The second that came before the sentences that stayed.

469
00:19:27,600 --> 00:19:27,840
Row.

470
00:19:28,400 --> 00:19:28,640
What?

471
00:19:29,140 --> 00:19:30,560
Are you sure it didn't come?

472
00:19:30,980 --> 00:19:32,860
Rowena stopped the cappuccino midway.

473
00:19:33,240 --> 00:19:34,380
The cup hung suspended.

474
00:19:35,040 --> 00:19:36,740
The heat rising to her face.

475
00:19:37,180 --> 00:19:37,960
What do you mean?

476
00:19:38,460 --> 00:19:38,820
Nothing.

477
00:19:38,820 --> 00:19:44,980
Marlo deflected and looked at the dark car across the street with an expression that was nothing.

478
00:19:45,440 --> 00:19:46,060
Never mind.

479
00:19:46,520 --> 00:19:47,540
But the sentence stayed.

480
00:19:48,200 --> 00:19:51,120
Marlo knew how to put sentences in the air the way they'd hang suspended.

481
00:19:51,640 --> 00:19:53,320
And this one stayed the rest of the coffee.

482
00:19:53,760 --> 00:19:54,900
The rest of the way back.

483
00:19:55,140 --> 00:19:56,300
The rest of the whole afternoon.

484
00:19:57,020 --> 00:19:59,880
Rowena returned to the house near the river in the late afternoon,

485
00:20:00,380 --> 00:20:03,740
with savanna's golden light striking the paving stones from the side.

486
00:20:04,200 --> 00:20:08,800
And a thin mist rising from the river as it always did when the heat began to give way.

487
00:20:08,820 --> 00:20:12,120
The two men followed behind in professional silence.

488
00:20:12,720 --> 00:20:14,600
Jago was still at the downtown office.

489
00:20:15,040 --> 00:20:16,040
The house was quiet.

490
00:20:16,660 --> 00:20:17,800
Only neither in the kitchen.

491
00:20:18,360 --> 00:20:20,900
Cutting something with that silent precision of hers.

492
00:20:21,300 --> 00:20:25,720
And the smell of rosemary coming from some pot that had been on the stove for a while.

493
00:20:26,120 --> 00:20:28,280
Rowena went into Jago's private study,

494
00:20:28,660 --> 00:20:31,640
with an excuse she'd prepared for herself while still in the car.

495
00:20:32,080 --> 00:20:34,900
She needed that old contract from the house renovation work.

496
00:20:35,280 --> 00:20:38,200
The carpenter had asked for a copy of the original specification.

497
00:20:38,200 --> 00:20:40,020
It was a polite lie.

498
00:20:40,340 --> 00:20:43,240
The kind you tell yourself before doing what you were going to do anyway.

499
00:20:43,760 --> 00:20:44,940
She opened the first drawer.

500
00:20:45,420 --> 00:20:51,960
Office papers all in order, labelled with the precision of a man who tolerated chaos on no surface.

501
00:20:52,740 --> 00:20:53,380
Second drawer.

502
00:20:54,000 --> 00:20:54,520
Contracts.

503
00:20:54,760 --> 00:20:56,620
Thin folders with dates and numbers.

504
00:20:57,200 --> 00:20:58,000
Third drawer.

505
00:20:58,380 --> 00:20:59,340
A cream-coloured envelope.

506
00:20:59,860 --> 00:21:00,820
No return address.

507
00:21:01,360 --> 00:21:04,900
With her name in the center in the impersonal, type-written handwriting.

508
00:21:05,520 --> 00:21:07,380
Let her head in the upper right corner.

509
00:21:07,380 --> 00:21:10,140
Winslow foundation for independent journalism.

510
00:21:10,800 --> 00:21:11,880
The envelope was open.

511
00:21:12,180 --> 00:21:13,080
She stood still.

512
00:21:13,520 --> 00:21:15,680
The study itself went still around her.

513
00:21:15,860 --> 00:21:18,920
The dark shelves, the books lined up by size.

514
00:21:19,320 --> 00:21:23,400
The narrow window that looked out onto the side garden with the moss on the stones.

515
00:21:23,960 --> 00:21:25,760
Her hands went strangely quiet.

516
00:21:26,140 --> 00:21:27,080
She took the envelope.

517
00:21:27,480 --> 00:21:29,160
She pulled out the contents carefully,

518
00:21:29,660 --> 00:21:32,480
as if the paper might confirm something she already knew.

519
00:21:32,780 --> 00:21:34,120
But didn't yet want to name.

520
00:21:34,620 --> 00:21:35,360
Two sheets.

521
00:21:35,360 --> 00:21:37,420
The first was the formal invitation.

522
00:21:38,120 --> 00:21:38,800
A job offer.

523
00:21:39,220 --> 00:21:43,460
A series of long investigative reports, full grant, complete autonomy over the topics.

524
00:21:44,040 --> 00:21:46,640
An offer that would bring her career back to life from scratch.

525
00:21:47,120 --> 00:21:49,540
At the exact point where she'd left off before Savannah.

526
00:21:50,180 --> 00:21:50,940
Before the ball.

527
00:21:51,360 --> 00:21:52,060
Before everything.

528
00:21:52,720 --> 00:21:54,660
The second sheet was a carbon copy.

529
00:21:55,140 --> 00:21:55,740
A reply.

530
00:21:56,320 --> 00:21:57,740
Dated 10 days ago.

531
00:21:58,160 --> 00:21:58,900
Dear Serz.

532
00:21:59,400 --> 00:22:01,260
We thank you for your generous consideration.

533
00:22:01,940 --> 00:22:05,220
At this time, Miss Pike is not available to take on new professional

534
00:22:05,220 --> 00:22:05,820
commitments.

535
00:22:06,560 --> 00:22:07,560
We renew our thanks.

536
00:22:08,120 --> 00:22:10,080
A signature at the bottom in hand writing.

537
00:22:10,680 --> 00:22:14,040
The same handwriting that appeared in the notes he left her in the kitchen in the morning.

538
00:22:14,580 --> 00:22:17,300
The same as the contract she signed alongside him.

539
00:22:17,480 --> 00:22:21,260
The same one she'd learned to recognize before even reading what was written.

540
00:22:21,740 --> 00:22:22,620
His hand writing.

541
00:22:23,160 --> 00:22:26,220
Ruinna kept looking at the sheet for a length of time she couldn't measure.

542
00:22:26,740 --> 00:22:27,860
Her body didn't tremble.

543
00:22:28,240 --> 00:22:29,760
Her body went very still.

544
00:22:30,100 --> 00:22:32,560
And the stillness was heavier than any tremor.

545
00:22:32,960 --> 00:22:34,680
Ruinna put the envelope back in the drawer.

546
00:22:34,680 --> 00:22:37,420
Closed it with the same care she'd opened it.

547
00:22:37,600 --> 00:22:40,600
She left the private study without taking the carpenters contract.

548
00:22:40,960 --> 00:22:42,280
She didn't need the contract.

549
00:22:42,620 --> 00:22:43,420
She never had.

550
00:22:43,800 --> 00:22:44,960
She went to the living room.

551
00:22:45,300 --> 00:22:46,300
She sat on the sofa.

552
00:22:46,720 --> 00:22:47,900
Without turning on the light.

553
00:22:48,400 --> 00:22:52,920
The afternoon had closed into that dark blue of early night that came fast in Savannah's summer.

554
00:22:53,400 --> 00:22:55,340
And the room filled with a warm dimness.

555
00:22:55,740 --> 00:22:57,440
On the other side next to the big window.

556
00:22:57,960 --> 00:22:59,940
The empty chair was in its usual place.

557
00:23:00,300 --> 00:23:02,760
With the last light of day reaching only the backrest.

558
00:23:02,760 --> 00:23:05,440
She looked at the chair for a long time.

559
00:23:05,740 --> 00:23:07,440
Two stories she thought.

560
00:23:07,980 --> 00:23:11,620
One of them has a short old name that no one pronounces inside this house.

561
00:23:11,980 --> 00:23:15,980
The other has his handwriting on a sheet that answered for her without her knowing.

562
00:23:16,520 --> 00:23:17,240
The phone rang.

563
00:23:17,620 --> 00:23:18,460
It was Jago.

564
00:23:19,020 --> 00:23:19,260
Love.

565
00:23:19,800 --> 00:23:21,200
I'm not going to make it home yet.

566
00:23:21,620 --> 00:23:22,460
Don't stay hungry.

567
00:23:23,020 --> 00:23:24,060
Eat without me.

568
00:23:24,380 --> 00:23:25,340
She closed her eyes.

569
00:23:25,800 --> 00:23:27,600
She held her voice in the right place.

570
00:23:27,900 --> 00:23:32,200
That exact place where the voice stops trembling and becomes just an answer.

571
00:23:32,200 --> 00:23:33,040
Okay.

572
00:23:33,560 --> 00:23:34,340
I love you.

573
00:23:34,600 --> 00:23:35,140
You too.

574
00:23:35,540 --> 00:23:36,220
She hung up.

575
00:23:36,440 --> 00:23:37,860
She kept the phone in her hand.

576
00:23:38,260 --> 00:23:40,140
The heat of the device against her palm.

577
00:23:40,640 --> 00:23:44,620
Outside the river ran with that low constant sound she'd learned to find calming

578
00:23:44,620 --> 00:23:46,280
and that now sounded different.

579
00:23:46,760 --> 00:23:47,940
The empty chair waited.

580
00:23:48,560 --> 00:23:50,400
And for the first time in six months,

581
00:23:50,820 --> 00:23:52,800
Rowena Pike felt inside her own chest.

582
00:23:53,240 --> 00:23:56,040
The low firm creek of a decision beginning to be made.

583
00:23:56,500 --> 00:24:01,260
The cream envelope sat on the table between them as if it weighed more than the wood holding it up.

584
00:24:01,260 --> 00:24:03,940
Rowena had waited all day to set it down there.

585
00:24:04,140 --> 00:24:06,540
At the exact spot where he usually left his keys.

586
00:24:07,000 --> 00:24:11,440
She chose the dining room table because it was the only room where Jago couldn't lean on a

587
00:24:11,440 --> 00:24:12,020
work object.

588
00:24:12,500 --> 00:24:14,620
No paper, no pen, no phone.

589
00:24:14,940 --> 00:24:18,140
Just him, her and his handwriting betraying his handwriting.

590
00:24:18,840 --> 00:24:20,200
Jago came in after eight.

591
00:24:20,460 --> 00:24:24,160
He took off his jacket with the slowness of someone who already knew what he'd find.

592
00:24:24,460 --> 00:24:27,840
The house near the Savannah River smelled of Jasmine from the garden outside.

593
00:24:27,840 --> 00:24:33,760
An out of season's sweetness that only worsened the sensation that the air was breathing on its own.

594
00:24:33,960 --> 00:24:34,900
He saw the envelope.

595
00:24:35,340 --> 00:24:36,660
He didn't ask what it was.

596
00:24:37,060 --> 00:24:40,360
Inside he felt a lying sentence form before he could stop it.

597
00:24:40,520 --> 00:24:44,200
I was going to tell you and in the same instant, new it was false.

598
00:24:44,580 --> 00:24:45,660
He wasn't going to.

599
00:24:45,800 --> 00:24:49,560
If she hadn't found it, that paper would have died at the bottom of that drawer.

600
00:24:50,080 --> 00:24:53,060
Rowena, his voice came out too controlled to be sincere.

601
00:24:53,440 --> 00:24:54,860
It's not what it looks like.

602
00:24:55,140 --> 00:24:57,140
She crossed her arms over her linen dress.

603
00:24:57,140 --> 00:24:58,400
She didn't sit.

604
00:24:58,680 --> 00:25:01,700
The yellow light of the chandelier fell between them like a border.

605
00:25:02,120 --> 00:25:03,980
It's exactly what it looks like Jago.

606
00:25:04,420 --> 00:25:05,460
He breathed in deep.

607
00:25:05,920 --> 00:25:08,460
The cold panic settled between one rib and another.

608
00:25:08,820 --> 00:25:12,020
That old cold he knew from another night, 10 years ago.

609
00:25:12,420 --> 00:25:14,540
He swallowed twice before he managed to speak.

610
00:25:14,980 --> 00:25:16,460
I wanted to protect you.

611
00:25:16,660 --> 00:25:17,520
From a job offer.

612
00:25:17,880 --> 00:25:21,260
From an offer that was going to take you away from Savannah for six months.

613
00:25:21,720 --> 00:25:23,180
Rowena smiled without joy.

614
00:25:23,660 --> 00:25:26,240
And the decision to go or stay was yours.

615
00:25:26,240 --> 00:25:28,560
He opened his mouth and found no answer.

616
00:25:28,960 --> 00:25:31,700
She continued lower because the low voice hurt more.

617
00:25:32,080 --> 00:25:33,000
You answered for me.

618
00:25:33,060 --> 00:25:34,680
You said, thank you for me.

619
00:25:34,880 --> 00:25:36,140
You declined for me.

620
00:25:36,520 --> 00:25:39,600
Each sentence fell like a small stone into the bottom of a glass.

621
00:25:40,040 --> 00:25:41,280
And then you brought me breakfast.

622
00:25:41,920 --> 00:25:42,180
Rowena.

623
00:25:42,840 --> 00:25:43,100
No.

624
00:25:43,600 --> 00:25:44,580
She raised her hand.

625
00:25:45,020 --> 00:25:47,260
And her hand was trembling and she hated that.

626
00:25:47,500 --> 00:25:49,100
You're not going to ask me for time.

627
00:25:49,640 --> 00:25:51,900
Time is the one thing you shouldn't ask for today.

628
00:25:52,280 --> 00:25:53,560
You had six months.

629
00:25:54,020 --> 00:25:55,380
He took a step toward her.

630
00:25:55,380 --> 00:25:56,820
She took a step back.

631
00:25:57,060 --> 00:25:58,160
It was a small movement.

632
00:25:58,640 --> 00:26:01,980
But he felt as if he'd been shoved against the opposite wall of the room.

633
00:26:02,500 --> 00:26:03,940
Inside something in him.

634
00:26:04,320 --> 00:26:07,360
The part that was always certain began to crack.

635
00:26:07,800 --> 00:26:11,720
He watched her mouth pronounce the next sentence before he heard it.

636
00:26:11,860 --> 00:26:12,600
Who is kit?

637
00:26:13,060 --> 00:26:16,260
The name fell to the dining room floor and stayed there gleaming.

638
00:26:16,760 --> 00:26:18,040
Jego looked at the envelope.

639
00:26:18,580 --> 00:26:19,460
looked at her.

640
00:26:19,580 --> 00:26:22,440
looked at the window that faced the dark river outside.

641
00:26:22,900 --> 00:26:23,660
He said nothing.

642
00:26:23,660 --> 00:26:26,700
And his silence was the first real confession.

643
00:26:27,400 --> 00:26:28,080
Good night, Jego.

644
00:26:28,620 --> 00:26:29,960
She went up the stairs slowly.

645
00:26:30,440 --> 00:26:34,580
He stood beside the table for too long listening to her footsteps disappear into the upstairs

646
00:26:34,580 --> 00:26:35,100
hallway.

647
00:26:35,600 --> 00:26:40,300
Then he sat in the nearest chair elbows on his knees and stared at his own envelope as if the

648
00:26:40,300 --> 00:26:42,360
paper were capable of answering for him.

649
00:26:42,760 --> 00:26:43,720
Rowena didn't sleep.

650
00:26:44,120 --> 00:26:47,520
She spent the small hours with her eyes open at the ceiling of the guest room.

651
00:26:47,900 --> 00:26:51,980
That room she'd never entered before and where the sheets smelled of forgotten lavender.

652
00:26:51,980 --> 00:26:55,100
She mentally repeated the list of things she knew.

653
00:26:55,420 --> 00:26:57,380
The name, the chair, the terrace.

654
00:26:58,000 --> 00:27:00,580
Udora's remark about a laugh that wasn't hers.

655
00:27:01,060 --> 00:27:02,820
The payments she hadn't yet traced.

656
00:27:03,240 --> 00:27:04,880
The envelope answered in his handwriting.

657
00:27:05,540 --> 00:27:07,040
There were two stories being hidden.

658
00:27:07,440 --> 00:27:09,040
She needed to unravel both.

659
00:27:09,480 --> 00:27:13,240
In the morning before the sun rose fully, she called a taxi from the street.

660
00:27:13,580 --> 00:27:15,080
She didn't ask for a house car.

661
00:27:15,400 --> 00:27:16,400
She didn't tell Filan.

662
00:27:16,900 --> 00:27:21,580
She put on the plane as close she had and went out the side door and no guard saw her.

663
00:27:21,580 --> 00:27:24,820
Because no guard expected her to leave before six in the morning.

664
00:27:25,420 --> 00:27:30,820
Silas Ashford's office was in downtown Savannah in an old townhouse with tall windows and a

665
00:27:30,820 --> 00:27:32,740
permanent smell of coffee and old paper.

666
00:27:33,180 --> 00:27:36,100
The sun hadn't yet warm the sidewalk when she climbed the steps.

667
00:27:36,700 --> 00:27:38,280
Silas answered the door himself.

668
00:27:38,680 --> 00:27:39,960
He didn't even ask what she wanted.

669
00:27:40,400 --> 00:27:42,560
He just pointed to the chair in front of the desk.

670
00:27:43,000 --> 00:27:44,660
You already know why I'm here.

671
00:27:44,900 --> 00:27:46,080
I'm pretty sure I do.

672
00:27:46,540 --> 00:27:48,420
Silas poured two coffees without asking.

673
00:27:48,960 --> 00:27:50,980
And I'm pretty sure I shouldn't open my mouth.

674
00:27:50,980 --> 00:27:54,260
Roena accepted the coffee and didn't drink it.

675
00:27:54,660 --> 00:27:57,560
Silas, her voice came out firmer than she expected.

676
00:27:58,140 --> 00:27:59,700
Your his friend, I know that.

677
00:28:00,040 --> 00:28:04,160
But you were also the only one who looked me in the eye that night at the ball and didn't pretend

678
00:28:04,160 --> 00:28:05,660
not to see what you were seeing.

679
00:28:06,040 --> 00:28:07,700
I need to know who kit is.

680
00:28:08,160 --> 00:28:10,300
Silas let the coffee rest between his hands.

681
00:28:10,760 --> 00:28:15,680
He stared at the tabletop for long enough that Roena understood the answer would hurt him too.

682
00:28:16,000 --> 00:28:16,980
Kit was his brother.

683
00:28:17,380 --> 00:28:17,980
He said it last.

684
00:28:17,980 --> 00:28:19,020
Younger.

685
00:28:19,380 --> 00:28:19,660
Was.

686
00:28:20,240 --> 00:28:21,700
That's what they say in Savannah.

687
00:28:22,340 --> 00:28:23,280
And what do you say?

688
00:28:23,820 --> 00:28:24,980
Silas raised his eyes.

689
00:28:25,340 --> 00:28:26,700
There was a new caution in them.

690
00:28:27,040 --> 00:28:29,940
The caution of someone crossing a line and knowing it.

691
00:28:30,120 --> 00:28:32,700
I say there was a boating accident 10 years ago

692
00:28:32,700 --> 00:28:37,080
that the boat was found destroyed, that the family buried a closed casket.

693
00:28:37,640 --> 00:28:40,360
He paused and that Jego never believed it.

694
00:28:40,700 --> 00:28:42,300
Roena felt her own chest drop.

695
00:28:42,640 --> 00:28:44,300
Why did he never believe it?

696
00:28:44,640 --> 00:28:45,940
Silas shook his head slowly.

697
00:28:45,940 --> 00:28:48,880
Roena, not today, not this.

698
00:28:49,340 --> 00:28:50,720
This isn't mine to tell.

699
00:28:51,380 --> 00:28:51,680
Silas.

700
00:28:52,160 --> 00:28:53,780
I've already said more than I should.

701
00:28:54,220 --> 00:28:55,120
He looked at the door.

702
00:28:55,400 --> 00:28:56,560
Go home ask him.

703
00:28:56,860 --> 00:28:57,820
He won't answer me.

704
00:28:58,080 --> 00:28:59,740
Then come back here when he doesn't.

705
00:29:00,060 --> 00:29:00,720
She got up.

706
00:29:01,000 --> 00:29:02,080
At the door she stopped.

707
00:29:02,560 --> 00:29:04,300
She didn't look back when she said.

708
00:29:04,540 --> 00:29:05,160
Thank you.

709
00:29:05,520 --> 00:29:06,480
Silas didn't answer.

710
00:29:07,000 --> 00:29:09,220
He kept looking at her coffee that hadn't been drunk.

711
00:29:09,740 --> 00:29:11,360
And for the first time in 10 years,

712
00:29:11,800 --> 00:29:13,960
he felt he might be betraying the right friend.

713
00:29:14,360 --> 00:29:15,600
Back at the house near the river.

714
00:29:15,600 --> 00:29:17,800
Roena found Neeve in the kitchen,

715
00:29:18,340 --> 00:29:20,720
arranging sprigs of basil in a glass jar.

716
00:29:21,100 --> 00:29:23,940
The old housekeeper had her hair pinned up in a loose bun

717
00:29:23,940 --> 00:29:26,380
and wore the same grey apron as always.

718
00:29:26,780 --> 00:29:29,740
Roena stopped in the doorway for a second before going in.

719
00:29:30,020 --> 00:29:33,420
Neeve belonged to that house more than Jego belonged to it.

720
00:29:33,640 --> 00:29:35,640
If anyone knew, it was her.

721
00:29:35,980 --> 00:29:36,340
Neeve.

722
00:29:36,820 --> 00:29:37,700
The woman looked up.

723
00:29:37,900 --> 00:29:40,380
She smiled with that small smile she kept for Roena.

724
00:29:40,940 --> 00:29:41,700
Good morning dear.

725
00:29:42,180 --> 00:29:43,180
Shall I make some tea?

726
00:29:43,600 --> 00:29:43,940
Neeve.

727
00:29:44,440 --> 00:29:44,920
Who is Kitt?

728
00:29:44,920 --> 00:29:47,000
The smile disappeared so fast

729
00:29:47,000 --> 00:29:49,280
that Roena almost doubted it had existed.

730
00:29:49,940 --> 00:29:51,820
Neeve's hands gripped the jar too hard.

731
00:29:52,360 --> 00:29:54,400
One of the sprigs slipped and fell into the sink.

732
00:29:54,980 --> 00:29:55,300
Oh dear.

733
00:29:55,820 --> 00:29:56,180
Please.

734
00:29:56,760 --> 00:29:58,680
Neeve looked at the door leading to the hallway.

735
00:29:59,120 --> 00:30:01,060
She looked at the window that faced the garden,

736
00:30:01,560 --> 00:30:03,540
where the morning Jasmine was still closed.

737
00:30:03,880 --> 00:30:07,040
She looked at the counter as if the answer might be printed on the marble.

738
00:30:07,360 --> 00:30:08,540
It's not my place.

739
00:30:08,960 --> 00:30:09,840
I know it isn't.

740
00:30:10,140 --> 00:30:11,460
Roena took a step closer,

741
00:30:11,960 --> 00:30:14,140
but I've been sleeping in this house for six months.

742
00:30:14,140 --> 00:30:16,920
And I can't pretend anymore that I don't see.

743
00:30:17,340 --> 00:30:18,420
He avoids the terrace.

744
00:30:19,000 --> 00:30:19,920
You avoid answering.

745
00:30:20,540 --> 00:30:23,020
Mrs. Udora has never said that name near me.

746
00:30:23,400 --> 00:30:24,940
And last night I asked my husband,

747
00:30:25,460 --> 00:30:27,900
the word slipped out before she could choose another.

748
00:30:28,160 --> 00:30:29,200
And he went silent.

749
00:30:29,820 --> 00:30:31,180
Neeve closed her eyes.

750
00:30:31,520 --> 00:30:32,700
He avoids the terrace.

751
00:30:33,200 --> 00:30:35,200
Her voice came out broken almost inaudible.

752
00:30:35,680 --> 00:30:38,060
Because that's where the boat set out that night.

753
00:30:38,460 --> 00:30:39,500
Roena didn't move.

754
00:30:39,840 --> 00:30:40,880
What night, Neeve?

755
00:30:41,060 --> 00:30:41,520
The night.

756
00:30:41,520 --> 00:30:43,600
Neeve wiped her hands on her apron,

757
00:30:43,880 --> 00:30:44,960
a mechanical gesture,

758
00:30:45,560 --> 00:30:46,420
the only night.

759
00:30:46,880 --> 00:30:48,980
The one this family could never buried properly.

760
00:30:49,480 --> 00:30:50,700
She turned her face aside.

761
00:30:51,180 --> 00:30:52,660
Don't ask me for the rest dear.

762
00:30:53,100 --> 00:30:53,420
Please.

763
00:30:54,020 --> 00:30:55,260
Roena swallowed hard.

764
00:30:55,700 --> 00:30:56,900
Mr. Kitt,

765
00:30:57,000 --> 00:30:57,900
Neeve continued.

766
00:30:58,480 --> 00:31:00,960
And now she was speaking to the basil, not to her.

767
00:31:01,220 --> 00:31:02,380
At a way of laughing loud.

768
00:31:02,840 --> 00:31:06,640
Mrs. Udora used to say he'd wake the whole house when he was a child.

769
00:31:07,140 --> 00:31:09,260
A small smile crossed her face and vanished.

770
00:31:09,260 --> 00:31:12,420
It was a beautiful laugh, too full for that mouth.

771
00:31:12,900 --> 00:31:13,720
You have his laugh.

772
00:31:14,360 --> 00:31:15,500
Roena had to grip the counter.

773
00:31:16,140 --> 00:31:17,400
The air went out of her slowly.

774
00:31:18,020 --> 00:31:19,920
Her hand pressed on the cold marble.

775
00:31:20,380 --> 00:31:24,700
The certainty assembling inside her ribs like an old building rising from the dark.

776
00:31:25,100 --> 00:31:26,060
Whose laugh it was.

777
00:31:26,420 --> 00:31:27,820
Where the sentence came from.

778
00:31:28,020 --> 00:31:30,080
Why Udora had looked at her that way,

779
00:31:30,380 --> 00:31:32,160
as she left that night at the ball.

780
00:31:32,580 --> 00:31:33,540
Thank you, Neeve.

781
00:31:33,860 --> 00:31:36,420
Dear, the housekeeper held her arm for a second.

782
00:31:36,840 --> 00:31:38,660
Her fingers were firm and dry.

783
00:31:38,660 --> 00:31:39,600
He suffered.

784
00:31:40,160 --> 00:31:41,900
Don't let anger make you forget that.

785
00:31:42,100 --> 00:31:42,860
I won't forget.

786
00:31:43,400 --> 00:31:45,720
The weekend passed in a silence of war.

787
00:31:46,140 --> 00:31:47,920
Jego didn't try to enter the guest room.

788
00:31:48,340 --> 00:31:49,840
Roena didn't come down from meals.

789
00:31:50,420 --> 00:31:52,220
Feeling carried trays in silence.

790
00:31:52,760 --> 00:31:53,960
Left them outside the door.

791
00:31:54,360 --> 00:31:55,520
Collected them untouched.

792
00:31:56,160 --> 00:31:57,100
On Saturday afternoon,

793
00:31:57,740 --> 00:31:58,980
Roena wrote in her planner.

794
00:31:59,420 --> 00:32:01,320
The list of everything she needed to trace.

795
00:32:01,860 --> 00:32:02,280
Payments.

796
00:32:02,940 --> 00:32:03,320
Names.

797
00:32:03,840 --> 00:32:04,020
Cities.

798
00:32:04,820 --> 00:32:05,200
Dates.

799
00:32:05,680 --> 00:32:08,340
She started with the public library in downtown Savannah.

800
00:32:08,340 --> 00:32:11,180
Where the old newspapers were kept on microfilm.

801
00:32:11,580 --> 00:32:14,640
She spent hours hunched over a reader that hummed softly.

802
00:32:15,120 --> 00:32:19,020
The smell of dry paper and old air conditioning filling the small room.

803
00:32:19,320 --> 00:32:21,220
She found the headline she knew existed.

804
00:32:21,740 --> 00:32:23,800
Quint Air Missing After Coastal Storm.

805
00:32:24,300 --> 00:32:26,140
The photo was small, grainy.

806
00:32:26,600 --> 00:32:28,680
A young man smiling with his mouth open.

807
00:32:28,980 --> 00:32:30,120
His teeth a little crooked.

808
00:32:30,580 --> 00:32:32,360
His hair touseled by the wind.

809
00:32:32,700 --> 00:32:34,640
She looked at the face for a long time.

810
00:32:34,940 --> 00:32:36,660
There was something of Jego in it.

811
00:32:36,660 --> 00:32:39,180
In the shape of the eyes in the line of the jaw.

812
00:32:39,640 --> 00:32:41,260
There was also that Frank Lough,

813
00:32:41,480 --> 00:32:42,400
Nive had described.

814
00:32:42,920 --> 00:32:46,160
Two wide for a newspaper portrait, impossible to contain.

815
00:32:46,780 --> 00:32:49,420
On Sunday, she cross-referenced information.

816
00:32:49,860 --> 00:32:52,340
She asked feeling for old statements with some excuse.

817
00:32:52,920 --> 00:32:56,060
And the assistant, who already liked her more than he should,

818
00:32:56,320 --> 00:32:57,600
gave in without asking.

819
00:32:57,980 --> 00:33:01,640
She found regular payments going out of a parallel account of Jego's.

820
00:33:01,880 --> 00:33:02,320
Monthly.

821
00:33:02,760 --> 00:33:04,340
Always the same rounded amount.

822
00:33:04,340 --> 00:33:08,340
Always to the office of a lawyer with no recognizable family name.

823
00:33:08,720 --> 00:33:12,420
She found receipts from a pharmacy in a small town she'd never heard of.

824
00:33:12,560 --> 00:33:16,900
She found, among the clippings, Nive kept in an old envelope in the kitchen cabinet.

825
00:33:17,480 --> 00:33:21,280
A photo where a teenage kid appeared beside an older man.

826
00:33:21,720 --> 00:33:24,500
The same face she'd recognized in the more recent records.

827
00:33:25,000 --> 00:33:26,840
Marlo called at three in the morning on Monday.

828
00:33:27,340 --> 00:33:28,900
Rowena answered on the second ring.

829
00:33:29,360 --> 00:33:31,800
Row I had the strange feeling that you needed to laugh.

830
00:33:32,320 --> 00:33:32,660
Marlo.

831
00:33:32,660 --> 00:33:34,820
Seriously, I was asleep.

832
00:33:35,320 --> 00:33:37,780
woke up out of nowhere, looked at the ceiling and thought,

833
00:33:38,280 --> 00:33:40,500
this woman needs to laugh right now.

834
00:33:40,860 --> 00:33:41,580
Rowena laughed.

835
00:33:41,900 --> 00:33:45,520
She laughed for real mouth open in the middle of the silent guest room.

836
00:33:45,900 --> 00:33:50,420
Then she started to cry and kept laughing and Marlo on the other end stayed quiet,

837
00:33:50,780 --> 00:33:52,280
waiting for the hurricane to pass.

838
00:33:52,720 --> 00:33:55,540
I found out the name, Rowena said when she was able.

839
00:33:56,040 --> 00:33:57,900
The kid guy, he was his brother.

840
00:33:58,460 --> 00:33:58,720
Was.

841
00:33:59,260 --> 00:34:00,560
That's what Silas said.

842
00:34:00,560 --> 00:34:03,440
Marlo breathed in deep and do you believe it?

843
00:34:03,720 --> 00:34:06,360
I believe nobody pays for a pharmacy for a dead man.

844
00:34:06,820 --> 00:34:08,080
Silas on the other end.

845
00:34:08,960 --> 00:34:09,620
Then, Row.

846
00:34:10,220 --> 00:34:11,880
Marlo's voice was serious now.

847
00:34:12,180 --> 00:34:14,120
Are you sure you want to go down this hole?

848
00:34:14,500 --> 00:34:15,460
I already have.

849
00:34:15,760 --> 00:34:16,640
Then hold on tight.

850
00:34:17,180 --> 00:34:21,420
Rowena looked at the planner open on the mattress and a dress had appeared twice in the

851
00:34:21,420 --> 00:34:24,520
receipts, a small town a few hours by train from Savannah.

852
00:34:25,000 --> 00:34:27,140
A name that matched the man from the old photo.

853
00:34:27,140 --> 00:34:31,500
She circled everything in red pen and underlined the address three times.

854
00:34:31,900 --> 00:34:34,620
The pressure of the pen leaving a groove on the paper below.

855
00:34:35,120 --> 00:34:39,480
On the other side of the house, Jago was sitting in the study with a glass of whiskey he hadn't

856
00:34:39,480 --> 00:34:40,260
touched in hours.

857
00:34:40,720 --> 00:34:42,360
He'd heard the taxi arrive in the morning.

858
00:34:42,840 --> 00:34:44,000
He'd heard the taxi leave.

859
00:34:44,340 --> 00:34:46,520
He'd heard Rowena ask feeling for the statements.

860
00:34:47,120 --> 00:34:49,900
With an excuse he knew because he himself was the one.

861
00:34:50,200 --> 00:34:52,180
Who'd used that excuse decades ago.

862
00:34:52,680 --> 00:34:54,100
He knew she was piecing it together.

863
00:34:54,540 --> 00:34:56,220
He knew she was going to find it.

864
00:34:56,220 --> 00:35:00,720
And for the first time in 10 years he couldn't tell whether he was afraid of what she'd

865
00:35:00,720 --> 00:35:03,780
discover or afraid of what he'd feel when she knew.

866
00:35:04,040 --> 00:35:05,560
He ran his hand over his forehead.

867
00:35:06,040 --> 00:35:06,980
His hand was trembling.

868
00:35:07,620 --> 00:35:10,140
In the guest room Rowena closed the planner.

869
00:35:10,520 --> 00:35:10,960
A name.

870
00:35:11,480 --> 00:35:11,980
An address.

871
00:35:12,620 --> 00:35:13,440
A small town.

872
00:35:13,780 --> 00:35:15,140
Everything that had come before.

873
00:35:15,580 --> 00:35:19,600
The old story, the charade at the ball, the coffee without a recorder, had been

874
00:35:19,600 --> 00:35:20,860
training for this decision.

875
00:35:21,280 --> 00:35:22,340
She turned off the light.

876
00:35:22,860 --> 00:35:26,140
And in the dark, she heard clearly the sound the empty chair made

877
00:35:26,140 --> 00:35:27,220
inside her now.

878
00:35:27,460 --> 00:35:28,660
It was no longer a creek.

879
00:35:29,040 --> 00:35:30,100
It was a whole name.

880
00:35:30,660 --> 00:35:32,280
Silas gave in on Tuesday morning.

881
00:35:32,700 --> 00:35:34,840
And he gave in because Rowena stopped asking.

882
00:35:35,340 --> 00:35:37,160
She walked into his office without knocking.

883
00:35:37,600 --> 00:35:39,560
She placed the open planner on his desk.

884
00:35:39,960 --> 00:35:41,400
The address circled in red.

885
00:35:41,900 --> 00:35:45,060
The name of the man from the old photo written beside it.

886
00:35:45,160 --> 00:35:45,960
She said nothing.

887
00:35:46,640 --> 00:35:47,540
Silas read it.

888
00:35:47,720 --> 00:35:50,260
Lean back against the chair and closed his eyes for a moment.

889
00:35:50,640 --> 00:35:55,140
Like someone who knew this moment would come sooner or later and had chosen too late.

890
00:35:55,140 --> 00:35:56,920
You got to this on your own.

891
00:35:57,140 --> 00:35:59,320
I get to almost everything on my own Silas.

892
00:35:59,860 --> 00:36:00,760
The open his eyes.

893
00:36:00,880 --> 00:36:02,080
There was guilt in them now.

894
00:36:02,400 --> 00:36:07,060
An old guilty no longer tried to disguise beneath the efficiency of the faithful assistant.

895
00:36:07,560 --> 00:36:09,080
If I complete the picture.

896
00:36:09,640 --> 00:36:10,800
Jago will kill me.

897
00:36:11,160 --> 00:36:13,820
Jago is already dying inside Silas.

898
00:36:14,280 --> 00:36:15,940
She said, what do you want?

899
00:36:16,320 --> 00:36:17,460
To bury both of them.

900
00:36:17,880 --> 00:36:22,520
Silas kept looking at her for a length of time that seemed to stretch beyond how long silence

901
00:36:22,520 --> 00:36:23,520
usually lasts.

902
00:36:23,520 --> 00:36:27,740
Then he opened a desk drawer and took out a small card no letterhead.

903
00:36:28,120 --> 00:36:31,880
With a name written by hand on one side and an address on the other.

904
00:36:32,240 --> 00:36:34,280
He slid it across the desk with two fingers.

905
00:36:34,840 --> 00:36:36,580
Like someone handing something over.

906
00:36:36,900 --> 00:36:39,860
And at the same time apologizing for having taken so long.

907
00:36:40,280 --> 00:36:42,300
The man who carries the money is this one.

908
00:36:42,540 --> 00:36:44,820
His voice came out low, almost horse.

909
00:36:45,260 --> 00:36:47,060
He lives between Savannah and the town.

910
00:36:47,400 --> 00:36:49,420
He makes the trip by train once a month.

911
00:36:49,660 --> 00:36:50,960
Always on the first Saturday.

912
00:36:51,360 --> 00:36:52,640
He tapped the card lightly.

913
00:36:52,640 --> 00:36:55,220
Kid lives in that town under another name.

914
00:36:55,580 --> 00:36:56,820
I'm not going to tell you which.

915
00:36:57,220 --> 00:36:58,800
That he'll have to tell you himself.

916
00:36:59,380 --> 00:37:00,260
Roenah took the card.

917
00:37:00,640 --> 00:37:02,520
She felt the paper way more than it should.

918
00:37:02,860 --> 00:37:05,120
More than any paper card should weigh.

919
00:37:05,440 --> 00:37:06,260
Thank you.

920
00:37:06,660 --> 00:37:09,740
Roenah Silas leaned forward his elbows on the desk.

921
00:37:10,140 --> 00:37:12,260
If he doesn't want to come back, don't force it.

922
00:37:12,420 --> 00:37:13,180
He has that right.

923
00:37:13,600 --> 00:37:14,820
I won't force it.

924
00:37:15,060 --> 00:37:15,620
And please.

925
00:37:16,100 --> 00:37:18,820
His voice nearly broke before reaching the end of the sentence.

926
00:37:19,320 --> 00:37:21,360
Take care of Jago when you come back.

927
00:37:21,360 --> 00:37:24,400
She tucked the card into the inside pocket of her bag.

928
00:37:24,720 --> 00:37:25,520
She stood up.

929
00:37:25,720 --> 00:37:27,860
She was almost at the door when he spoke again.

930
00:37:28,400 --> 00:37:28,880
Roenah.

931
00:37:29,320 --> 00:37:29,560
Yes.

932
00:37:30,140 --> 00:37:32,220
By now, why did you tell me now?

933
00:37:32,560 --> 00:37:33,740
He took a while to answer.

934
00:37:34,180 --> 00:37:36,280
When he answered, he looked at the window.

935
00:37:36,700 --> 00:37:37,500
Not at her.

936
00:37:37,800 --> 00:37:40,580
At the street below where Savannah went on ahead, knowing nothing.

937
00:37:41,060 --> 00:37:44,260
Because I watched Jago spend 10 years dying slowly.

938
00:37:44,640 --> 00:37:47,420
And I watched you arrive and him start to live again.

939
00:37:47,700 --> 00:37:50,560
And I can't watch him lose you thinking he's protecting you.

940
00:37:50,560 --> 00:37:52,260
He turned his gaze back to her.

941
00:37:52,540 --> 00:37:54,100
Someone needs to break this cycle.

942
00:37:54,540 --> 00:37:56,740
You're the only one with the courage to break it.

943
00:37:57,040 --> 00:37:58,180
Roenah nodded once.

944
00:37:58,620 --> 00:37:59,080
She left.

945
00:37:59,620 --> 00:38:03,120
Outside Savannah's air had that humid mid-afternoon heat.

946
00:38:03,500 --> 00:38:04,580
Dense and green.

947
00:38:05,060 --> 00:38:08,640
With the smell of wet earth mixed with the distant salt of the estuary.

948
00:38:09,020 --> 00:38:10,780
She walked to the station without hurry,

949
00:38:11,360 --> 00:38:13,320
feeling the uneven paving under her shoes.

950
00:38:13,920 --> 00:38:15,540
The sounds of the city around her.

951
00:38:15,740 --> 00:38:17,260
The streetcar passing by.

952
00:38:17,520 --> 00:38:19,320
A child shouting in some backyard.

953
00:38:19,320 --> 00:38:21,900
The clinking of glasses in a corner cafe.

954
00:38:22,420 --> 00:38:24,560
She bought a one-way ticket for the four-a-clock train.

955
00:38:25,060 --> 00:38:26,600
And called Marlo from the payphone.

956
00:38:27,080 --> 00:38:27,660
I'm going.

957
00:38:28,180 --> 00:38:28,340
Alone?

958
00:38:28,980 --> 00:38:29,280
Alone?

959
00:38:29,980 --> 00:38:31,780
Marlo paused for a long time.

960
00:38:32,140 --> 00:38:35,000
The kind that contains questions one decides not to ask.

961
00:38:35,380 --> 00:38:39,040
Do you want me to call someone if you don't come back in 24 hours?

962
00:38:39,300 --> 00:38:40,020
Call Silas.

963
00:38:40,520 --> 00:38:40,800
Done.

964
00:38:41,360 --> 00:38:41,980
Before boarding.

965
00:38:42,540 --> 00:38:44,360
Roenah stopped at the house near the river.

966
00:38:44,640 --> 00:38:46,260
She came in through the side door.

967
00:38:46,540 --> 00:38:49,280
Went up to the guest room through some clothes into a small suit

968
00:38:49,920 --> 00:38:53,460
with the objectivity of someone who knows that thinking too much

969
00:38:53,460 --> 00:38:55,780
is a luxury that doesn't fit in the luggage.

970
00:38:56,420 --> 00:39:00,660
She went down to the kitchen, where the afternoon light came in slanted through the shutters.

971
00:39:01,160 --> 00:39:03,360
And Ruth in stripes across the stone floor.

972
00:39:03,820 --> 00:39:06,200
And wrote a short letter on a piece of writing paper.

973
00:39:06,620 --> 00:39:08,000
The letter had a single line.

974
00:39:08,380 --> 00:39:10,980
I'll come back when I bring what he couldn't bring on his own.

975
00:39:11,260 --> 00:39:13,300
She left the letter on top of the day's newspaper.

976
00:39:13,760 --> 00:39:14,280
She left.

977
00:39:14,820 --> 00:39:17,420
Feel and saw her come down the stairs with the suitcase

978
00:39:17,420 --> 00:39:18,540
and ask nothing.

979
00:39:18,540 --> 00:39:20,440
She asked him to call a taxi.

980
00:39:21,040 --> 00:39:21,780
He called one.

981
00:39:22,160 --> 00:39:26,080
Before the taxi door closed, the assistant said quietly almost to himself,

982
00:39:26,560 --> 00:39:27,620
have a good trip miss.

983
00:39:27,960 --> 00:39:29,040
She didn't correct him.

984
00:39:29,440 --> 00:39:31,820
The train left Savannah at four o'clock sharp.

985
00:39:32,400 --> 00:39:36,700
Roenah chose a seat by the window and rested her forehead against the cold glass.

986
00:39:37,180 --> 00:39:38,940
And for a long time thought about nothing.

987
00:39:39,380 --> 00:39:45,140
She passed low houses, flooded fields, a smaller town with a rusty water tower in the center.

988
00:39:45,580 --> 00:39:46,760
A river that wasn't the Savannah.

989
00:39:46,760 --> 00:39:51,340
A line of Cyprus's cutting into the copper-colored sky of the late afternoon.

990
00:39:51,960 --> 00:39:53,640
The sun began to set slowly,

991
00:39:54,160 --> 00:39:56,800
tinting the landscape and orange that looked like a painting.

992
00:39:57,320 --> 00:40:00,000
She opened the planner and re-read the address three times

993
00:40:00,000 --> 00:40:01,740
as if she could forget it.

994
00:40:01,900 --> 00:40:03,180
And she knew she couldn't.

995
00:40:03,520 --> 00:40:05,440
On the other side at the house near the river,

996
00:40:06,020 --> 00:40:10,860
Jago arrived at seven at night and felt that something was missing before he looked in any direction.

997
00:40:11,340 --> 00:40:13,340
It was as if the house had changed weight,

998
00:40:13,700 --> 00:40:15,600
not temperature, not sound,

999
00:40:15,600 --> 00:40:16,400
weight.

1000
00:40:17,000 --> 00:40:18,780
He passed through the living room the kitchen,

1001
00:40:19,340 --> 00:40:20,880
saw the letter on top of the newspaper.

1002
00:40:21,540 --> 00:40:22,360
He read it.

1003
00:40:22,540 --> 00:40:23,420
He read it again.

1004
00:40:23,920 --> 00:40:27,820
And something in him collapsed with the same silent precision of a structure

1005
00:40:27,820 --> 00:40:31,500
that gives way from within with no visible warning.

1006
00:40:31,900 --> 00:40:34,620
It was the same old night returning to his nostrils,

1007
00:40:35,180 --> 00:40:36,820
the smell of the sea after the storm,

1008
00:40:37,340 --> 00:40:38,800
the taste of metal in his mouth,

1009
00:40:39,260 --> 00:40:41,920
the physical animal certainty that he had lost again

1010
00:40:41,920 --> 00:40:45,840
and that this time the punishment was proportional to the size of the mistake.

1011
00:40:46,380 --> 00:40:47,440
He let the letter drop.

1012
00:40:47,760 --> 00:40:49,080
He sat on the kitchen floor.

1013
00:40:49,540 --> 00:40:50,280
He truly sat.

1014
00:40:50,620 --> 00:40:52,580
His back against the door of the low cabinet

1015
00:40:52,580 --> 00:40:56,840
and his hands open on his knees as if he didn't know what to do with them.

1016
00:40:57,000 --> 00:40:59,020
He stayed there too long for it to be dignity.

1017
00:40:59,480 --> 00:41:01,120
Scytler showed up half an hour later.

1018
00:41:01,560 --> 00:41:03,520
He hadn't been called, he simply knew.

1019
00:41:03,860 --> 00:41:05,280
He came in through the side door,

1020
00:41:05,700 --> 00:41:06,860
found Jago on the floor,

1021
00:41:07,000 --> 00:41:08,540
knelt beside him without hesitation.

1022
00:41:09,220 --> 00:41:10,040
I told her.

1023
00:41:10,040 --> 00:41:12,180
Jago raised his face slowly.

1024
00:41:12,660 --> 00:41:14,900
There was something in his eyes that wasn't anger.

1025
00:41:15,360 --> 00:41:17,020
It was an exhaustion so deep,

1026
00:41:17,280 --> 00:41:18,740
it passed beneath the anger

1027
00:41:18,740 --> 00:41:21,380
and reached a place the anger no longer reached.

1028
00:41:21,900 --> 00:41:22,840
You told her what?

1029
00:41:23,180 --> 00:41:24,700
The name, the address.

1030
00:41:25,240 --> 00:41:26,960
The man who carries the money.

1031
00:41:27,440 --> 00:41:28,600
Jago closed his eyes.

1032
00:41:28,980 --> 00:41:30,940
It took him a full second to breathe again.

1033
00:41:31,340 --> 00:41:32,520
I'm going to hit you, Scytler.

1034
00:41:33,040 --> 00:41:33,740
Hit me.

1035
00:41:34,040 --> 00:41:35,140
Jago didn't hit him.

1036
00:41:35,440 --> 00:41:39,460
He clenched his fist, raised it and the fist stopped in the air before touching anything.

1037
00:41:39,460 --> 00:41:42,820
He lowered his hand slowly, rested it on his knee

1038
00:41:42,820 --> 00:41:46,620
and stared at his own fingers as if he didn't recognize them.

1039
00:41:46,780 --> 00:41:49,060
As if that man sitting on the floor of his kitchen

1040
00:41:49,060 --> 00:41:50,360
belonged to someone else.

1041
00:41:50,760 --> 00:41:51,600
She went alone.

1042
00:41:52,060 --> 00:41:52,680
She did.

1043
00:41:53,020 --> 00:41:54,400
And if he doesn't take her in.

1044
00:41:54,720 --> 00:41:55,700
He'll take her in.

1045
00:41:56,020 --> 00:41:57,660
He can't say no to anyone, Jago.

1046
00:41:58,220 --> 00:41:59,020
He never could.

1047
00:41:59,340 --> 00:42:00,580
Jago swallowed twice.

1048
00:42:01,000 --> 00:42:03,340
And if he takes her in and doesn't want to come?

1049
00:42:03,600 --> 00:42:04,580
Scytler didn't answer.

1050
00:42:05,020 --> 00:42:06,180
There was no answer to that.

1051
00:42:06,580 --> 00:42:08,140
Jago squeezed his eyes shut.

1052
00:42:08,140 --> 00:42:11,440
Inside something in him was reconstructing the timeline

1053
00:42:11,440 --> 00:42:13,280
with a precision that hurt.

1054
00:42:13,700 --> 00:42:17,320
The train's schedule, the distance, the time she'd need to arrive.

1055
00:42:17,880 --> 00:42:21,440
The night she'd spend alone in a town he knew from a map and from receipts.

1056
00:42:21,800 --> 00:42:23,120
But never with his own eyes.

1057
00:42:23,680 --> 00:42:24,380
He'd never gone.

1058
00:42:24,760 --> 00:42:26,360
He'd never allowed himself to go.

1059
00:42:26,620 --> 00:42:28,080
And now she was going for him.

1060
00:42:28,340 --> 00:42:30,260
With the courage he'd traded for control.

1061
00:42:30,740 --> 00:42:34,880
And he was sitting on the kitchen floor because he no longer knew what to do with his own body.

1062
00:42:35,440 --> 00:42:35,700
Scytler.

1063
00:42:36,360 --> 00:42:36,720
Yes.

1064
00:42:36,720 --> 00:42:39,380
If she comes back, I'll fix it.

1065
00:42:39,680 --> 00:42:40,440
She'll come back.

1066
00:42:40,820 --> 00:42:42,040
If she comes back.

1067
00:42:42,340 --> 00:42:44,860
Silas rested his hand on his shoulder and left it there.

1068
00:42:45,080 --> 00:42:45,980
She'll come back, Jago.

1069
00:42:46,480 --> 00:42:49,500
In the small town the train arrived at 9.20 at night.

1070
00:42:50,020 --> 00:42:54,100
Rowing a got off with the small suitcase felt the asphalt different under her feet.

1071
00:42:54,660 --> 00:42:59,500
Piotr without Sivanor's constant noise and looked for a small hotel a block from the station,

1072
00:42:59,960 --> 00:43:03,980
with painted wooden windows and a ceiling fan that turned slowly.

1073
00:43:03,980 --> 00:43:05,640
She paid for one night.

1074
00:43:06,020 --> 00:43:06,600
Went up.

1075
00:43:06,880 --> 00:43:07,580
Didn't have dinner.

1076
00:43:08,060 --> 00:43:09,960
She sat on the edge of the bed until dawn,

1077
00:43:10,320 --> 00:43:13,200
with Silas's card in her hand and the address memorized.

1078
00:43:13,780 --> 00:43:16,180
In the morning she followed the map on foot.

1079
00:43:16,640 --> 00:43:18,240
The town was smaller than she'd expected.

1080
00:43:18,820 --> 00:43:20,300
A main street with five shops.

1081
00:43:20,800 --> 00:43:24,420
A central square with a bandstand painted white and peeling at the edges.

1082
00:43:24,840 --> 00:43:28,400
Low houses scattered along dirt roads where grass grew down the middle.

1083
00:43:28,740 --> 00:43:31,520
The address led her to a modest light blue house,

1084
00:43:31,520 --> 00:43:36,120
with an neglected front garden and a rocking chair sitting motionless on the porch.

1085
00:43:36,720 --> 00:43:37,680
She knocked on the door.

1086
00:43:38,100 --> 00:43:39,660
Once with her knuckle, firm.

1087
00:43:40,240 --> 00:43:41,400
A man opened it.

1088
00:43:41,620 --> 00:43:43,660
She recognized him before she looked properly.

1089
00:43:44,120 --> 00:43:46,200
She recognized him by the shape of the eyes.

1090
00:43:46,640 --> 00:43:47,860
By the line of the jaw.

1091
00:43:48,300 --> 00:43:49,780
By the way he stood in the doorway.

1092
00:43:50,400 --> 00:43:55,700
The same way Jago had a filling a threshold that presence that filled the space even in silence.

1093
00:43:56,360 --> 00:43:59,100
Except this man was thinner, harder.

1094
00:43:59,100 --> 00:44:02,940
With a small scar crossing his left eyebrow and lighter hair.

1095
00:44:03,280 --> 00:44:03,880
Sun bleached.

1096
00:44:04,440 --> 00:44:07,680
He had the slightly crooked teeth she remembered from the newspaper photo.

1097
00:44:08,500 --> 00:44:08,520
Kit.

1098
00:44:09,180 --> 00:44:10,980
He was paralyzed for a full second.

1099
00:44:11,380 --> 00:44:12,880
Then he stepped back half a step.

1100
00:44:13,240 --> 00:44:14,100
Who are you?

1101
00:44:14,440 --> 00:44:15,260
Rowena Pike.

1102
00:44:15,680 --> 00:44:16,560
She didn't move forward.

1103
00:44:17,040 --> 00:44:18,600
I've been with your brother for a while.

1104
00:44:19,080 --> 00:44:21,240
The silence that came after was dense and loaded.

1105
00:44:21,820 --> 00:44:23,680
Kit rested one hand on the door frame.

1106
00:44:24,000 --> 00:44:25,240
As if he needed the support.

1107
00:44:25,720 --> 00:44:27,620
His fingers gripping the painted wood.

1108
00:44:27,620 --> 00:44:29,140
You shouldn't be here.

1109
00:44:29,320 --> 00:44:29,860
I know.

1110
00:44:30,240 --> 00:44:30,960
He sent you.

1111
00:44:31,300 --> 00:44:32,880
He doesn't even know I came.

1112
00:44:33,260 --> 00:44:34,640
Kit looked at her for a long time.

1113
00:44:35,040 --> 00:44:36,780
The physical shock was still in him.

1114
00:44:37,100 --> 00:44:38,640
And the old anger rose automatically.

1115
00:44:39,240 --> 00:44:41,500
And the fear hidden beneath the anger too.

1116
00:44:41,780 --> 00:44:42,980
And there was something else.

1117
00:44:43,300 --> 00:44:43,780
Deeper.

1118
00:44:44,100 --> 00:44:45,800
That he could no longer name well.

1119
00:44:46,080 --> 00:44:47,080
Then he stepped aside.

1120
00:44:47,640 --> 00:44:48,280
Come in.

1121
00:44:48,600 --> 00:44:50,420
The living room was small and clean.

1122
00:44:50,940 --> 00:44:54,120
With that silence of a place where a person has lived alone for too long.

1123
00:44:54,540 --> 00:44:55,880
There was a dark wooden table.

1124
00:44:55,880 --> 00:44:56,960
Two chairs.

1125
00:44:57,440 --> 00:44:59,680
A sofa with warm fabric on the backrest.

1126
00:45:00,180 --> 00:45:02,440
A shelf with few books and no ornaments.

1127
00:45:03,100 --> 00:45:04,640
Kit pointed to one of the chairs.

1128
00:45:05,180 --> 00:45:05,920
Rowena sat.

1129
00:45:06,300 --> 00:45:09,140
He stayed standing leaning against the wall arms crossed.

1130
00:45:09,620 --> 00:45:09,860
Talk.

1131
00:45:10,400 --> 00:45:10,920
She talked.

1132
00:45:11,420 --> 00:45:12,840
She talked for a long time.

1133
00:45:13,160 --> 00:45:14,760
Without embellishing without crying.

1134
00:45:15,200 --> 00:45:18,460
She talked about the investigators J. Go had hired over the years.

1135
00:45:18,920 --> 00:45:21,700
About the money he left with lawyers who had no names.

1136
00:45:22,220 --> 00:45:24,740
About the medications paid for by third parties.

1137
00:45:24,740 --> 00:45:27,420
The debts settled before they became dangerous.

1138
00:45:28,000 --> 00:45:31,620
About the empty chair no one explained and no one removed from the living room.

1139
00:45:31,880 --> 00:45:32,940
She talked about Yudora.

1140
00:45:33,520 --> 00:45:35,220
About the way she never said his name.

1141
00:45:35,720 --> 00:45:39,100
About the way once on the porch she had murmured about a lost laugh.

1142
00:45:39,460 --> 00:45:41,360
She talked about the terrace J. Go avoided.

1143
00:45:41,900 --> 00:45:43,780
She talked about the envelope he'd hidden.

1144
00:45:44,160 --> 00:45:46,540
About the control he confused with love.

1145
00:45:46,920 --> 00:45:50,080
About the old fear he carried because he thought that if he let go,

1146
00:45:50,320 --> 00:45:51,640
he'd lose everything again.

1147
00:45:52,100 --> 00:45:53,580
Kit listened without interrupting.

1148
00:45:53,580 --> 00:45:56,660
When she finished he stayed silent for a while.

1149
00:45:57,040 --> 00:45:57,740
Then he laughed.

1150
00:45:58,460 --> 00:45:59,900
A short dry laugh.

1151
00:46:00,320 --> 00:46:01,120
Almost a grunt.

1152
00:46:01,480 --> 00:46:03,220
He spent 10 years looking for me.

1153
00:46:03,460 --> 00:46:04,040
He did.

1154
00:46:04,360 --> 00:46:05,040
Without stopping.

1155
00:46:05,580 --> 00:46:06,240
Without stopping.

1156
00:46:06,860 --> 00:46:08,140
And he never came himself.

1157
00:46:08,560 --> 00:46:09,360
Rowena hesitated.

1158
00:46:09,840 --> 00:46:11,780
He thought you didn't want to be found by him.

1159
00:46:12,020 --> 00:46:13,080
Kit closed his eyes.

1160
00:46:13,580 --> 00:46:16,940
Inside something that had been hard for 10 years began to crack.

1161
00:46:17,440 --> 00:46:19,560
Slow and inevitable as a crack in stone.

1162
00:46:20,080 --> 00:46:20,960
He swallowed once.

1163
00:46:20,960 --> 00:46:21,920
Slow and again.

1164
00:46:22,520 --> 00:46:23,180
He wasn't wrong.

1165
00:46:23,700 --> 00:46:24,080
He was.

1166
00:46:24,640 --> 00:46:25,940
Rowena's voice came out lower.

1167
00:46:26,440 --> 00:46:27,820
He just didn't know he was.

1168
00:46:28,160 --> 00:46:29,820
Kit peeled himself off the wall.

1169
00:46:30,240 --> 00:46:31,140
He went to the window.

1170
00:46:31,680 --> 00:46:36,080
Looked at the neglected garden for a long time at the grass growing between the paving stones.

1171
00:46:36,540 --> 00:46:37,540
Then he turned around.

1172
00:46:37,960 --> 00:46:38,740
I'll make coffee.

1173
00:46:39,220 --> 00:46:41,120
They spent the afternoon and the night talking.

1174
00:46:41,620 --> 00:46:46,060
On the porch with cups that went cold twice and the sound of crickets filling the dark around them.

1175
00:46:46,280 --> 00:46:48,820
Kit spoke aloud for the first time about what he felt.

1176
00:46:48,820 --> 00:46:52,120
He said he'd fled because he thought he wasn't important to anyone.

1177
00:46:52,580 --> 00:46:56,200
But on that night, he'd asked his brother for help and his brother hadn't come.

1178
00:46:56,700 --> 00:47:00,700
And he understood in that instant that his world was worth less than a meeting.

1179
00:47:01,080 --> 00:47:05,680
That when the boat began to crack in the storm, he had two seconds to choose between swimming

1180
00:47:05,680 --> 00:47:06,340
or sinking.

1181
00:47:06,820 --> 00:47:09,760
And he chose to swim because the anger was greater than the exhaustion.

1182
00:47:10,420 --> 00:47:14,800
That when he came out the other side, on a stretch of beach he didn't even know where it was.

1183
00:47:15,240 --> 00:47:18,760
He made the decision to disappear because he thought no one would miss him enough to

1184
00:47:18,760 --> 00:47:19,480
really look.

1185
00:47:19,880 --> 00:47:24,260
And he looked, Kit said, looking at the bandstand in the square in the distance.

1186
00:47:24,840 --> 00:47:27,680
All these years, all these years.

1187
00:47:28,160 --> 00:47:30,100
Kit ran his hand over his eyes slowly.

1188
00:47:30,660 --> 00:47:32,480
He made a mistake out of fear, Kit.

1189
00:47:32,720 --> 00:47:33,600
Not out of choice.

1190
00:47:34,180 --> 00:47:37,120
Rowena spoke low, looking at the same point he was.

1191
00:47:37,400 --> 00:47:39,080
He's afraid of you all the time.

1192
00:47:39,260 --> 00:47:41,600
Of what happened and of what he didn't do.

1193
00:47:42,020 --> 00:47:46,740
Kit laughed again this time without the dryness of before, almost with affection.

1194
00:47:46,740 --> 00:47:49,760
And affection he clearly hadn't expected to feel.

1195
00:47:50,200 --> 00:47:52,720
You talk about him as if you knew him.

1196
00:47:52,960 --> 00:47:53,900
I know him.

1197
00:47:54,080 --> 00:47:54,860
You love him.

1198
00:47:55,100 --> 00:47:55,840
She didn't answer.

1199
00:47:56,340 --> 00:47:57,380
She didn't need to.

1200
00:47:57,680 --> 00:47:59,060
They stayed silent for a while.

1201
00:47:59,500 --> 00:48:02,580
With the warm wind passing through the branches of the old Magnolia,

1202
00:48:03,140 --> 00:48:04,660
growing in the corner of the garden.

1203
00:48:05,180 --> 00:48:07,780
Then Kit spoke, looking at his own hands.

1204
00:48:08,240 --> 00:48:10,260
If I come back, I come back once.

1205
00:48:10,760 --> 00:48:11,320
No promises.

1206
00:48:11,940 --> 00:48:13,940
If it doesn't work, I leave again.

1207
00:48:14,360 --> 00:48:16,260
And this time no one finds me.

1208
00:48:16,860 --> 00:48:17,340
Agreed.

1209
00:48:17,420 --> 00:48:19,580
And I don't know if I'll be able to look at him.

1210
00:48:19,900 --> 00:48:21,420
You don't need to know that now.

1211
00:48:21,780 --> 00:48:25,000
Kit nodded slowly, like someone making a deal with himself,

1212
00:48:25,400 --> 00:48:26,360
as much as with her.

1213
00:48:26,680 --> 00:48:28,200
In the morning he took a small suitcase.

1214
00:48:28,980 --> 00:48:29,600
Very small.

1215
00:48:30,120 --> 00:48:33,400
Rowena looked at that suitcase and understood the size of what he carried.

1216
00:48:33,940 --> 00:48:36,980
Not in what was inside, but in how little there was.

1217
00:48:37,480 --> 00:48:40,940
Before they left for the station, she sent a single message to Silas,

1218
00:48:41,340 --> 00:48:42,700
from the telegraph on the corner.

1219
00:48:43,180 --> 00:48:44,040
We arrived tomorrow.

1220
00:48:44,540 --> 00:48:45,280
Prepare you Dora.

1221
00:48:45,280 --> 00:48:49,420
While they waited for the train on the wooden bench of the town's only platform,

1222
00:48:50,040 --> 00:48:52,080
Kit looked at the horizon and said,

1223
00:48:52,440 --> 00:48:53,660
without turning his face.

1224
00:48:54,320 --> 00:48:54,680
Rowena.

1225
00:48:55,380 --> 00:48:55,780
Yes.

1226
00:48:56,360 --> 00:48:58,780
If you brought me here for him, he swallowed.

1227
00:48:59,380 --> 00:48:59,980
Thank you.

1228
00:49:00,240 --> 00:49:00,980
She didn't answer.

1229
00:49:01,460 --> 00:49:03,660
She simply rested her hand over his hand,

1230
00:49:03,940 --> 00:49:07,020
and his hand was cold, and hers was too.

1231
00:49:07,480 --> 00:49:09,040
The train whistled in the distance.

1232
00:49:09,660 --> 00:49:10,680
Jego didn't sleep.

1233
00:49:11,200 --> 00:49:13,540
The house near the Savannah River was so silent

1234
00:49:13,540 --> 00:49:16,000
that he could hear his own pulse in his throat.

1235
00:49:16,380 --> 00:49:18,480
Sitting on the study floor leaning against the shelf,

1236
00:49:18,900 --> 00:49:21,700
his suit rumbled and his tie loose since the small hours.

1237
00:49:22,260 --> 00:49:24,760
He counted time by the way the light came through the window.

1238
00:49:25,300 --> 00:49:26,940
First blue, then gray,

1239
00:49:27,260 --> 00:49:30,860
then a timid gold that arrived to insulting for the weight of the day.

1240
00:49:31,300 --> 00:49:33,420
Rowena's letter was still folded in his lap.

1241
00:49:33,760 --> 00:49:36,280
He no longer needed to reread it to know what was written.

1242
00:49:36,780 --> 00:49:39,480
I'll come back when I bring what he couldn't bring on his own.

1243
00:49:39,820 --> 00:49:41,720
Each word weighed more than the last.

1244
00:49:41,720 --> 00:49:44,840
Each word opened a door he'd kept closed for 10 years

1245
00:49:44,840 --> 00:49:47,540
and pushed him inside it with no choice, no warning,

1246
00:49:48,080 --> 00:49:49,780
without even letting him breathe first.

1247
00:49:50,260 --> 00:49:54,740
Inside, Jego had the cold certainty that the punishment had finally arrived,

1248
00:49:55,240 --> 00:49:58,140
not in the form of scandal, not in the form of death,

1249
00:49:58,520 --> 00:49:59,740
not in the form of a headline,

1250
00:50:00,320 --> 00:50:03,280
in the form of a woman with an ink scar in the Sunday paper,

1251
00:50:03,600 --> 00:50:05,840
going after what he hadn't had the courage to bring.

1252
00:50:06,180 --> 00:50:08,260
And in the most cowardly part of him,

1253
00:50:08,460 --> 00:50:10,740
a low voice said that this scar could open again,

1254
00:50:10,740 --> 00:50:13,520
that this time the woman too might not come back.

1255
00:50:13,980 --> 00:50:15,700
Silas came in at seven without knocking.

1256
00:50:16,180 --> 00:50:18,080
He brought coffee Jego hadn't asked for,

1257
00:50:18,300 --> 00:50:20,000
and a silenced Jego didn't want.

1258
00:50:20,440 --> 00:50:24,780
He stood in the door frame waiting with that lawyer's patience of someone who'd already seen too many

1259
00:50:24,780 --> 00:50:26,480
clients on the floor of his own office.

1260
00:50:27,020 --> 00:50:30,940
Talk, Jego said without looking up, she arrived, she's with him.

1261
00:50:31,180 --> 00:50:33,240
How do you know? She sent me a message.

1262
00:50:33,840 --> 00:50:38,300
Short, Silas hesitated, and at the bottom of that hesitation there was an old

1263
00:50:38,300 --> 00:50:41,660
lawyer had decided to carry in silence until now.

1264
00:50:41,880 --> 00:50:45,120
He held out the phone. Jego read the line on the screen

1265
00:50:45,120 --> 00:50:47,280
and took a full second to breathe again.

1266
00:50:47,840 --> 00:50:48,860
We arrived tomorrow.

1267
00:50:49,500 --> 00:50:51,900
Prepare you doorer. He closed his eyes.

1268
00:50:52,420 --> 00:50:55,180
He felt the room spin as if someone had flipped the floor.

1269
00:50:55,600 --> 00:50:59,240
There was a man inside him who wanted to yell at Silas for giving up the thread.

1270
00:50:59,740 --> 00:51:03,020
There was another deeper who wanted to kneel and give thanks.

1271
00:51:03,480 --> 00:51:05,260
The first one for half a second.

1272
00:51:05,260 --> 00:51:11,000
Jego stood up, grabbed Silas by the lapel, and stopped his fist in the air before it closed.

1273
00:51:11,540 --> 00:51:13,320
His hand trembled, it never trembled.

1274
00:51:13,860 --> 00:51:15,920
Don't hit, Silas said very low.

1275
00:51:16,260 --> 00:51:17,600
You're not a man who hits.

1276
00:51:18,000 --> 00:51:20,460
I'm not a man of anything right now, Jego answered,

1277
00:51:20,980 --> 00:51:24,440
and let go of the lapel like someone releasing a rope too hot to hold.

1278
00:51:24,840 --> 00:51:25,620
They stood still.

1279
00:51:26,140 --> 00:51:31,360
Outside a bird insisted on a whistle of three repeated notes without tiring, without mercy.

1280
00:51:31,880 --> 00:51:34,840
Jego looked at his own reflection in the glass of the picture frame.

1281
00:51:34,840 --> 00:51:40,700
And recognized neither the disheveled hair nor the civilized despair his eyes held.

1282
00:51:41,240 --> 00:51:44,440
Prepare her, he asked, and his voice didn't quite obey.

1283
00:51:45,000 --> 00:51:45,720
Prepare my mother.

1284
00:51:46,200 --> 00:51:46,620
I will.

1285
00:51:47,200 --> 00:51:47,620
Silas.

1286
00:51:48,100 --> 00:51:48,740
Jego swallowed.

1287
00:51:49,380 --> 00:51:49,920
Thank you.

1288
00:51:50,340 --> 00:51:51,520
Silas looked at him long.

1289
00:51:52,040 --> 00:51:52,660
He said nothing.

1290
00:51:53,260 --> 00:51:53,560
He left.

1291
00:51:54,060 --> 00:51:56,540
It was feeling who arrived first at the quint mentioned.

1292
00:51:57,120 --> 00:51:59,140
Udora was having tea in the small parlor.

1293
00:51:59,400 --> 00:52:02,140
The newspaper still untouched on the white linen napkin.

1294
00:52:02,140 --> 00:52:04,160
The matriarch looked up and read.

1295
00:52:04,500 --> 00:52:08,300
In the younger systems posture, that something was coming before the words.

1296
00:52:08,820 --> 00:52:09,640
She didn't ask.

1297
00:52:10,020 --> 00:52:10,560
She waited.

1298
00:52:11,080 --> 00:52:13,740
With that old skill of letting Silas do the work.

1299
00:52:14,120 --> 00:52:17,820
Mrs. Rowena asked that you come to the main hall at five.

1300
00:52:18,060 --> 00:52:22,260
Feline said, with the trained delicacy of someone delivering news he didn't understand.

1301
00:52:22,820 --> 00:52:24,340
And Mr. Jego as well.

1302
00:52:24,780 --> 00:52:27,880
Udora folded the newspaper carefully as if it might break.

1303
00:52:28,300 --> 00:52:31,560
A hand when it rested on the table had a strange lightness

1304
00:52:31,560 --> 00:52:32,820
for the weight of the day.

1305
00:52:33,040 --> 00:52:33,560
That's all?

1306
00:52:33,940 --> 00:52:34,860
She wanted to know.

1307
00:52:35,200 --> 00:52:35,860
That's all.

1308
00:52:36,160 --> 00:52:37,620
The matriarch didn't smile.

1309
00:52:38,040 --> 00:52:38,940
She didn't protest.

1310
00:52:39,460 --> 00:52:42,140
She nodded once and turned her gaze to the window.

1311
00:52:42,620 --> 00:52:45,700
Where the garden trees swade in a breeze no one inside could feel.

1312
00:52:46,140 --> 00:52:47,500
The trainer arrived at four.

1313
00:52:47,920 --> 00:52:51,740
Rowena got off on the savanna platform with the same small bag she'd left with.

1314
00:52:52,120 --> 00:52:56,120
And a thin man beside her who insisted on keeping three steps of distance.

1315
00:52:56,620 --> 00:53:00,980
Like someone still deciding whether to stay or turn around and disappear again.

1316
00:53:00,980 --> 00:53:02,580
Kit had his head down.

1317
00:53:02,900 --> 00:53:04,100
His cap pulled low.

1318
00:53:04,440 --> 00:53:07,100
His backpack held tight against his chest like a shield.

1319
00:53:07,620 --> 00:53:10,200
Every sudden noise in the station made his jaw clench.

1320
00:53:10,520 --> 00:53:12,360
He stopped twice on the way to the taxi.

1321
00:53:12,840 --> 00:53:15,480
And both times Rowena pretended not to see.

1322
00:53:16,080 --> 00:53:18,260
Continuing to walk at a pace that demanded nothing.

1323
00:53:18,820 --> 00:53:19,600
We can go back.

1324
00:53:19,840 --> 00:53:22,400
She said, at the third stop without pressure.

1325
00:53:22,880 --> 00:53:25,000
If you want to go back now, we go back.

1326
00:53:25,320 --> 00:53:28,000
I'll take you back and won't tell anyone you set foot in savanna.

1327
00:53:28,520 --> 00:53:29,100
Kit swallowed.

1328
00:53:29,620 --> 00:53:30,380
It's not that.

1329
00:53:30,380 --> 00:53:31,700
It's what then.

1330
00:53:31,900 --> 00:53:33,860
It's that I forgot what the smell is like.

1331
00:53:34,260 --> 00:53:35,320
Rowena looked at him.

1332
00:53:35,540 --> 00:53:41,320
There was an 18-year-old boy inside that thin man and the boy was blinking hard not to cry on the

1333
00:53:41,320 --> 00:53:43,260
sidewalk of a station full of strangers.

1334
00:53:43,720 --> 00:53:45,060
She didn't touch his arm.

1335
00:53:45,220 --> 00:53:47,120
She just stood there at the same height waiting.

1336
00:53:47,640 --> 00:53:49,340
The smell is the same, she answered.

1337
00:53:49,880 --> 00:53:51,440
Magnolia and old money.

1338
00:53:51,980 --> 00:53:52,520
Kit laughed.

1339
00:53:53,020 --> 00:53:54,900
A quick laugh almost a sob.

1340
00:53:55,320 --> 00:53:55,680
Ah.

1341
00:53:56,100 --> 00:53:57,080
So it's the same.

1342
00:53:57,400 --> 00:53:58,480
They got into the taxi.

1343
00:53:58,920 --> 00:54:01,040
Rowena told the driver to stop at the mansion.

1344
00:54:01,520 --> 00:54:02,840
Not at the house near the river.

1345
00:54:03,300 --> 00:54:05,280
Kit raised his face when the facade appeared.

1346
00:54:05,760 --> 00:54:09,140
That heavy iron gate he knew better than any other place in the world.

1347
00:54:09,540 --> 00:54:11,300
He stared at it for a long time.

1348
00:54:11,720 --> 00:54:16,280
A leaf came loose from one of the tall trees and fell on the hood of the car with a

1349
00:54:16,280 --> 00:54:17,540
lightness that seemed calculated.

1350
00:54:18,220 --> 00:54:19,200
No one said anything.

1351
00:54:19,620 --> 00:54:20,700
I don't know if I can.

1352
00:54:21,120 --> 00:54:21,780
Kit said, low.

1353
00:54:22,220 --> 00:54:23,300
You can make it to the door.

1354
00:54:23,840 --> 00:54:24,740
After that we decide.

1355
00:54:25,380 --> 00:54:27,760
And if they hate me, they don't hate you.

1356
00:54:27,760 --> 00:54:29,560
They don't know how to hate you.

1357
00:54:29,800 --> 00:54:30,580
Kit didn't answer.

1358
00:54:31,020 --> 00:54:32,840
The open the car door and got out slowly.

1359
00:54:33,280 --> 00:54:36,160
Like someone stepping onto a floor that might not hold his weight.

1360
00:54:36,620 --> 00:54:39,400
The main hall smelled of Magnolia and old money.

1361
00:54:39,820 --> 00:54:43,300
The afternoon came in through the tall windows in bands of golden light

1362
00:54:43,300 --> 00:54:46,360
that crossed the marble and stopped at the empty chair near the window

1363
00:54:46,360 --> 00:54:48,600
as if they knew exactly where to land.

1364
00:54:49,140 --> 00:54:50,380
Rowena went in first.

1365
00:54:50,840 --> 00:54:52,600
She deliberately chose that place.

1366
00:54:53,060 --> 00:54:55,780
Not the living room, not the library, not J. GO's study.

1367
00:54:55,780 --> 00:54:58,000
Where everything had begun to fall apart.

1368
00:54:58,480 --> 00:54:59,000
The hall.

1369
00:54:59,520 --> 00:55:04,840
The same room where one night, month earlier, a woman in a borrowed dress had held the face of a

1370
00:55:04,840 --> 00:55:08,240
silent man and kissed him in front of 300 people.

1371
00:55:08,620 --> 00:55:09,720
The smell was the same.

1372
00:55:10,200 --> 00:55:12,000
The light came in at the same angle.

1373
00:55:12,460 --> 00:55:13,780
The chair was still empty.

1374
00:55:14,440 --> 00:55:17,800
Rowena positioned herself exactly where she had stood on that other night.

1375
00:55:18,220 --> 00:55:20,400
As if she were marking a fixed point on a map.

1376
00:55:20,860 --> 00:55:22,320
Only she knew how to read.

1377
00:55:22,320 --> 00:55:25,760
Kit stayed one step behind, still in his cap,

1378
00:55:26,120 --> 00:55:28,720
still with his hand closed around the strap of the backpack.

1379
00:55:29,300 --> 00:55:30,660
Feeling opened the double doors.

1380
00:55:31,200 --> 00:55:32,440
Udora came in first.

1381
00:55:32,800 --> 00:55:36,400
The matriarch noticed Rowena, noticed the figure behind her.

1382
00:55:36,680 --> 00:55:41,780
And for a moment, tiny, almost invisible, her spine seemed to give way a millimeter.

1383
00:55:42,380 --> 00:55:43,460
She restrained it.

1384
00:55:43,600 --> 00:55:44,780
She kept her chin high.

1385
00:55:45,100 --> 00:55:47,660
She crossed the hall to the center and stopped, waiting.

1386
00:55:48,260 --> 00:55:49,440
J. GO came in after.

1387
00:55:49,980 --> 00:55:51,600
And his world stopped turning.

1388
00:55:51,600 --> 00:55:53,920
There was a thin man in the hall.

1389
00:55:54,360 --> 00:55:58,600
Then, with his cap pulled low, a small scar on his eyebrow.

1390
00:55:59,020 --> 00:56:01,780
His shoulders narrower than memory had drawn them.

1391
00:56:02,060 --> 00:56:06,940
A man who slowly lowered the cap, revealing his short hair, and looked up.

1392
00:56:07,100 --> 00:56:12,460
And it was the gaze of the 18-year-old boy, who had taken a boat out alone on a stormy night,

1393
00:56:12,740 --> 00:56:13,740
10 years before.

1394
00:56:14,220 --> 00:56:17,220
J. GO said nothing for a length of time no one there could measure.

1395
00:56:17,620 --> 00:56:19,000
He took a step than another.

1396
00:56:19,420 --> 00:56:20,040
Then he stopped.

1397
00:56:20,040 --> 00:56:23,000
Inside it was as if a dam had given way.

1398
00:56:23,360 --> 00:56:25,880
The old guilt, the anguish of the last two days.

1399
00:56:26,380 --> 00:56:31,300
The fear of losing Rowena, all mixing into a single hot point in the middle of his chest,

1400
00:56:31,640 --> 00:56:33,520
too hot to be born with composure.

1401
00:56:33,860 --> 00:56:35,020
He felt his throat tightened.

1402
00:56:35,500 --> 00:56:37,060
He felt his hands go cold.

1403
00:56:37,500 --> 00:56:40,440
He felt with brutal clarity that the punishment hadn't come.

1404
00:56:40,720 --> 00:56:44,240
That life, against any deserving, had given something back.

1405
00:56:44,560 --> 00:56:45,520
Kit, he said.

1406
00:56:45,960 --> 00:56:48,000
And his voice came out choked, ridiculous.

1407
00:56:48,000 --> 00:56:51,240
The voice of a big boy that didn't fit that man.

1408
00:56:51,680 --> 00:56:54,120
Kit, Kit dropped the backpack on the floor.

1409
00:56:54,540 --> 00:56:56,260
The thud was dry on the marble.

1410
00:56:56,740 --> 00:56:59,620
I ran away, he said, and his mouth trembled.

1411
00:57:00,120 --> 00:57:02,940
I ran away because I thought I wasn't important to anyone.

1412
00:57:03,420 --> 00:57:04,660
J. GO closed his eyes.

1413
00:57:05,260 --> 00:57:08,360
A tear fell before he could command his body to hold it back.

1414
00:57:08,660 --> 00:57:09,220
Then another.

1415
00:57:09,680 --> 00:57:10,680
He didn't wipe them.

1416
00:57:10,960 --> 00:57:12,720
I spent 10 years, he answered.

1417
00:57:13,220 --> 00:57:15,440
Trying to fix the worst choice of my life.

1418
00:57:15,760 --> 00:57:17,100
Kit shook his head incredulous.

1419
00:57:17,100 --> 00:57:19,220
And the shaking became a tremor.

1420
00:57:19,600 --> 00:57:21,980
And the tremor became a short dry sob.

1421
00:57:22,480 --> 00:57:24,920
J. GO crossed the rest of the hall in three strides,

1422
00:57:25,260 --> 00:57:27,360
and hugged his brother any which way.

1423
00:57:27,800 --> 00:57:29,640
A crooked hug without elegance,

1424
00:57:30,140 --> 00:57:32,420
without the composure all of Savannah knew.

1425
00:57:32,700 --> 00:57:34,920
A hug that had waited 10 years to happen,

1426
00:57:35,340 --> 00:57:38,540
and that now happened all at once, clumsy and urgent.

1427
00:57:39,200 --> 00:57:40,620
Kit was slow to return it.

1428
00:57:40,960 --> 00:57:43,400
When he did, he gripped J. GO's coat,

1429
00:57:43,660 --> 00:57:45,780
as if he were holding on so as not to fall.

1430
00:57:45,780 --> 00:57:48,060
J. GO's coat was not to fall.

